item_list.name: Tyrannosaurus Dino Bone
item_list.description: Mr Felton would definitely be interested in a specimen like this!

item_list.name: Triceratops Dino Bone
item_list.description: A Triceratops Fibula Dinosaur Bone!  Boy, Felton would be really interested in this!

item_list.name: Pterodactyl Dino Bone
item_list.description: Very Tiny Pterodactyl Dinosaur bone fragments.  Felton will certainly want to see them!

item_list.name: Karina's Clean Blankie
item_list.description: A freshly cleaned worn and tattered pink child's blanket.  Looks like it's been loved to death.  The owner would surely want this back!

item_list.name: Karina's Dirty Blankie
item_list.description: A worn and tattered pink child's blanket covered in mud!.  Looks like it's been loved to death.  The owner would likely not want it back all covered in mud!

item_list.name: Crate of Oranges
item_list.description: A wooden crate full of fresh oranges special for Dixie.

item_list.name: Pitted Horse Date
item_list.description: A small natural treat, sure to please any horse.

item_list.name: Horse Candy
item_list.description: Alfalfa coated in a candy shell, sure to make a horse happy,  and even a little more alert!

item_list.name: Hot Bran Mash
item_list.description: This Warm Treat not only makes a horse happy,  but the special mix of herbs and flavoring give the horse a boost of energy,  waking it right up!

item_list.name: Bag of Oats
item_list.description: Bag of whole Oats with a light mixing of molasses. Should fill a hungry horse.

item_list.name: Bag of Alfalfa Mix
item_list.description: Bag of alfalfa, soft green oat straw and clover with a light oil and molasses coating. Will fill even a starving horse,  they like it too!

item_list.name: Mouse
item_list.description:
A small white fuzzy rodent, with pink ears. The mouse is a quiet companion.
[ BONUS: +4 to all horse stats ]

item_list.name: Spider
item_list.description:
A small and easy to care for companion. Some say that spiders have the ability to communicate with horses.
[ BONUS: +2 to all horse stats ]

item_list.name: Rat
item_list.description:
A smarter, larger rodent than a mouse, rats are known for their intelligence and could be helpful with problem solving.
[ BONUS: +6 to all horse stats ]

item_list.name: Horseshoe Charm
item_list.description: This little charm is made of the same steel the farriers in Horse Isle use to shod the horses' hooves.  Despite how little it is, it was obviously made with great care.  A thick strip of leather tied tightly around it turns the little charm into a necklace made special for Sasha.

item_list.name: Vial of Medicine
item_list.description: The little vial holds some sweet smelling liquid that will hopefully help Dalton.  Hope it tastes as good as it smells!

item_list.name: Big Sandwich
item_list.description: This tasty sandwich is piled high with meat and veggies.  It was made just for Lars.  Everyone knows what an appetite farriers have!

item_list.name: Ryland's Bow
item_list.description: Crafted from strong, but flexible willow wood, Ryland's bow is obviously the tool of a skill hunter.  He probably misses it, and would like it returned to him.

item_list.name: Package of Hot Cocoa Mix
item_list.description: Abigail made this hot chocolate just for Heinrich.  It's wrapped in a soft white cloth, and tied with string.  Better hurry and give it to Heinrich.

item_list.name: Abigail's Ice skates
item_list.description: These white ice skates blend in perfectly with the snow on the ground.  No wonder Abigail lost them!  They are obviously loved, so they should probably be returned to their owner soon.

item_list.name: Gerbil
item_list.description:
There's no problem having this rodent around. This gerbil is cute and knows some jokes that your horse might enjoy.
[ BONUS: +6 to all horse stats ]

item_list.name: Crystal Statue
item_list.description: This beautiful statue was crafted from crystal, but cut in such a way to make it appear as if it was made from ice and snow.  The figure is that of a horse running with the wind!

item_list.name: Guinea Pig
item_list.description:
A squat, tan and white guinea pig. A gentle, playful rodent perfect for a horse's friend.
[ BONUS: +8 to all horse stats ]

item_list.name: Parrot
item_list.description:
A colorful, talkative parrot. Neither you or your horse will be lonely with this companion around.
[ BONUS: +17 to all horse stats ]

item_list.name: Pigeon
item_list.description:
A silvery feathered pigeon will keep your horse relaxed with its soft cooing.

item_list.name: Holli Daysin's Poem
item_list.description:
Go to the island of the rare hare
Pick up an egg that's beyond compare.
Go to the land where lava flows with might
Retrieve a carving of stone, the color of night.
Go to the land of the holiday snow
Get from its most famous resident something to show.
Go to where Pirates keep to their own
Then find an item that's etched on a bone.
Go to the land of cacti and heat
Bring back a painting of sand that's really neat.

item_list.name: Carlotta's Statement
item_list.description:
These are the notes you made after talking to Carlotta:
Joaquin loves milk.
Jose loves hot cocoa.
Javier loves salty snacks.
Jacinta adores tart drinks.
Juanita loves graham crackers.
Javier loves what Jose likes to drink.
Julianna hates marshmallows and cotton candy.
Javier won’t touch anything the girls eat or drink.
Joaquin can’t stand what Julianna eats or drinks.
Javier won’t touch what Joaquin or Julio eat or drink.
Julio loves cotton candy and what Jacinta loves to drink.
Neither Julianna or Juanita like what Jacinta eats or drinks.
One of the kids likes only things the other siblings don’t like.
Jacinta doesn’t like anything Joaquin or Javier eats or drinks.
Neither Jacinta or Joaquin will touch what Jose eats or drinks.
Jose doesn’t like what Julio, Julianna or Juanita eats or drinks.
Each kid likes only one kind of drink, and only one kind of dessert.

item_list.name: Jack's Last Letter
item_list.description:
To Hanska Hennig, former prima ballerina of the Whiskerton Ballet, now departing to places unknown.
Dearest Hans, I so regret that I couldn't say goodbye before I left. My thoughts have spiraled around and around. But the company said I must take occupancy immediately if I wanted the position- and you know how I have loathed feeling useless all these years. The sea breeze is invigorating- I haven't felt so good in a very long time. You must visit me someday soon, Hans- this is a lovely place, almost wild except for the few settlers other than myself. Until I see you again, I remain, Yours, Jack

item_list.name: Mysterious Letter
item_list.description:
Wed Compass Rose to Clouds afar
Then halve again twice more
Open wide and start anew
Wed Pirate’s Hat to Compass Rose
then halve again once more
Against a light- map’s backside to you
Clouds are seen in bottom right
The epicenter vertex is numbered zero
Number vertex from the center out
1 2 3 Left and 1 2 3 Right
1 2 3 Up and 1 2 3 Down
To solve future mysteries that unfold
For now the epicenter holds the prize

Isaac - 2 dozen oyster shells
Vega - 6 dozen corn husks
Twyla - oil of orange

item_list.name: Dozen Corn Husks
item_list.description: These tan crinkled and dried up husks are perfect for tamales. Vega will be pleased.

item_list.name: Oil of Orange
item_list.description: Made from orange peels, this sweet smelling oil is just what Twyla wanted.

item_list.name: Clouds Book
item_list.description: This nonfiction book is filled with pictures and information about different types of clouds. Ociel should be pleased.

item_list.name: Oyster Shell
item_list.description: Iridescent Mother of Pearl lines this oyster shell in a rainbow of colors. Isaac will be pleased.

item_list.name: Crate of Minorca Fowl
item_list.description: These dark feathered chickens do great in a hot & humid climate. Perfect for Dog Isle!

item_list.name: Bit of Dried Seaweed
item_list.description: Dark ocean green with a distinct brine smell.  The strange scratches must be a secret message for Dursley.

item_list.name: Coati
item_list.description:
This curious, long-tailed coati has amazing balance.
[ BONUS: +85 to all horse stats ]

item_list.name: Small Strange Chest
item_list.description:
A mysterious small carved wooden chest with no visible
way to open it. It is darkened from being buried in the lava
fields and marked with strange runes. Maybe someone
on this island can tell you about it.

item_list.name: Strange Black Package
item_list.description: A black so dark that it seems to absorb all light, this package is both heavy and ice cold. Best get it to Hyrokkin before it does something strange!

item_list.name: Bit of Marked Up Seaweed
item_list.description: Dark ocean green with a distinct brine smell. Dursley has added to the strange scratches. Must be a secret message for Ebenezer.

item_list.name: Crock of Utensils
item_list.description: Made of the finest quality stainless steel, this set of cooking utensils would make any chef happy. Jeremy should be pleased.

A basic saddle designed after that which is used by the Royal Canadian Mounted Police.
[ BONUS: +10 Agility ]

item_list.name: RCMP Saddle Pad

A simple saddle pad designed to fit under the saddle fashioned after that which is used by the Royal Canadian Mounted Police.
[ BONUS: +10 Endurance ]

item_list.name: RCMP Bridle
item_list.description:
A simple bridle designed after that which is used by the Royal Canadian Mounted Police.
[ BONUS: +10 Strength ]

item_list.name: Brown Paper Package
item_list.description: Svetlana's embroidery packaged for shipping.

item_list.name: Packet of Notes
item_list.description: Olena's outgoing mail.

item_list.name: Pysanky in a Case
item_list.description: Lesia's beautiful Pysanky egg in a hand carved case made by Vasyl.

item_list.name: Plush Triceratops
item_list.description:
A soft, adorable stuffed triceratops to help your horse sleep.
[ BONUS: +1 to all horse stats ]

item_list.name: Ostrich
item_list.description:
If you have a horse who could use a little exercise, this ostrich hen is perfect! She can match any horse for speed!
[ BONUS: +125 to all horse stats ]

item_list.name: Crate of Baby Chicks
item_list.description: 1/2 dozen baby Partridge Penedesenca chickens. Perfect for a hot climate like Hat Isle.

item_list.name: Bag of Chicken Feed
item_list.description: Filled with corn kernels, field peas, oats and barley, this feed should be perfect for chickens on a Pirate island.

item_list.name: Bag of Charcoal Powder
item_list.description: This black dust looks very messy! Hopefully it'll take care of the swamp stench for the Tropicton residents.  Cerise especially.

item_list.name: Skein of Spider's Silk
item_list.description: Loops of shimmering white spider's silk. You wonder what the witch wants with this.

item_list.name: Gryphon Egg Shard
item_list.description: A rather large and broken bit of a Gryphon's eggshell.

item_list.name: Tuft of Fur
item_list.description: Wiry, coarse (and stinky) brown hair from Grendel's hide. You hope this makes the witch happy.

item_list.name: Repaired Gryphon's Egg
item_list.description: The pieces have been transformed into a whole Gryphon's Egg. You hope the witch will accept this.

item_list.name: Curse Reversal Potion
item_list.description: A small vial of glowing magenta slime. You hope this works on poor Beltran!

item_list.name: Aye-aye
item_list.description:
This lemur is inquisitive and entertaining for any horse.
[ BONUS: +90 to all horse stats ]

item_list.name: Snowy Owl
item_list.description:
A very white, bright eyed snowy owl.
[ BONUS: +19 to all horse stats ]

item_list.name: Odd Purple Key
item_list.description: This shimmering purple key is bent in odd angles.

item_list.name: Odd Iron Key
item_list.description: This Iron Key is much larger than the other keys, and bent in crazy shapes. Hopefully, Madame Babushka will know what to do with it.

item_list.name: Fiddle Bow
item_list.description: Curtis' bow has broken strings hanging from it.

item_list.name: Repaired Fiddle Bow
item_list.description: The bow has new white horse hairs and has been rosined. Curtis will be pleased!

item_list.name: Chipmunk
item_list.description:
This friendly, busy rodent has fancy stripes and is on a constant lookout.
[ BONUS: +6 to all horse stats ]

item_list.name: Single Sock
item_list.description: A bit dirty from being buried, the sock is in otherwise fine shape. Mandy should be pleased.

transport_places.place_title: the southeastern tip of Jungle Isle

new_user.starting_message:
Welcome Newest Rider of Horse Isle!
Start by talking to Welcome Willy in the cabin. Click the TALK button by his name in the right hand window. He will know the location of a buried treasure on this island! Move to the spot he describes using the arrow keys. Then Click the WRENCH Icon at the lower right.

special_tiles.title: Earton Food Supply
special_tiles.description: Mr. Grits sells the best selection of food in the area. His store is always well stocked. Eli also happens to be the town historian!

special_tiles.title: Belinda Buckle's Gear Shop
special_tiles.description: Belinda offers simple, honest service here. You'll find all the basic gear for your horse along with straightforward advice.

special_tiles.title: Maggie's Garden
special_tiles.description:
There's an infestation of moles here!!
If you want to get rid of them, I'm sure she'd pay for the help.
^T5Wack the moles!^BMwackdamole^R1^T4View the top scores for this game^BSHWack Da Mole^R1^X^Z

special_tiles.title: Appleton Wagon Station
special_tiles.description: The sign reads "Welcome to the Appleton Wagon Station". You are pleased to see that they offer four different destinations and all for reasonable prices. You take a seat on the bench and consider your options.

special_tiles.title: Maggie's House
special_tiles.description: Maggie's walls are covered with her prized paintings. The paintings all depict magical places and magical beasts. You don't recognize the artist, but it seems Maggie is quite the fan!

special_tiles.title: Treeton Drawing Room
special_tiles.description:
In this cabin there is a giant easel with lots of pens. Everyone who enters is encouraged to go ahead and doodle alone or together.

DUE TO ABUSE - Only subscribers' drawings may be seen by other players.

special_tiles.title: Sarah Seams' Clothing Shop
special_tiles.description: Sarah tries to keep a wide selection of the latest, and cheapest, competition fashions available. Her shop is cramped however, and you keep banging your elbows on mannequins.

special_tiles.title: Speed Trainer
special_tiles.description: Train your horse for speed improvements.

special_tiles.title: Appleton Wishing Well
special_tiles.description: Welcome to the wishing well. Use your coins wisely.

special_tiles.title: Appleton Ponds
special_tiles.description: Take a breather here and rest your eyes a moment or watch the fish jump.

special_tiles.title: Appleton Ponds
special_tiles.description: Take a breather here and rest your eyes for a moment or watch the fish jump.

special_tiles.title: Farrier Franklin Forge
special_tiles.description: Franklin Forge has been doing horse related metalwork for many years right here in this shop. He pounds away on the anvil with a steady rhythm. A lot of his business is brought in from nearby farms.

special_tiles.title: Vet Kathy McKure
special_tiles.description: Kathy McKure will do everything she can to get your horse back to full health.

special_tiles.title: Appleton Blacksmith
special_tiles.description: Arthur the Appleton Blacksmith is proud of his store and of his craft. His shop has horseshoes of all kinds and sizes hanging on the wall.

special_tiles.title: Earton General Store
special_tiles.description: This is the perfect place to find all that you could ever need.  No more running around town to get all your supplies. You have heard that Simon is a bit fond of the ladies in town and they adore him too. You don't doubt this because he has a kind face and is absolutely charming. You feel like buying the whole store the minute you walk in.

special_tiles.title: Welcome to Treeton!
special_tiles.description: Welcome to the town of Treeton on Horse Isle. There is a lot to do here. Please enjoy your stay.^X^Z

special_tiles.title: Treeton Wagon Station
special_tiles.description: The Treeton Wagon Station is a quick way to get to both Earton and Appleton.  It's a whole lot faster than running, but you have to decide if it's worth the price.

special_tiles.title: Appleton Ponds
special_tiles.description: Enjoy the beautiful day and try your luck fishing here. Do take care around the swan though. This one likes to bite!

special_tiles.title: Earton Barns
special_tiles.description: You've entered the Earton Barns and they are very clean. Hay bales stacked up, water buckets full, and some lanterns hanging but no animals are in right now. If your horse is tired you can go ahead and let it relax here.

special_tiles.title: Welcome to Appleton!
special_tiles.description: Welcome to Appleton, traveler!  Our people are the friendliest you'll find!  Due to our fine health we imagine...  Apple a day and all!^X^Z

special_tiles.title: Prison Docks
special_tiles.description: Now that you have worked your way out of prison, you may have a free ride back to Earton.

special_tiles.title: Direction Sign
special_tiles.description:
NORTH: Horse Isle Equestrian Center
WEST: Appleton Docks
EAST: Bridge to Hoof Isle
SOUTH: Appleton
^X^Z

special_tiles.title: Earton Jumping Arena
special_tiles.description:
Compete against others in this competition  that is mainly based off your horse's Strength and Speed.  Only 6 horses can compete at one time.
Be careful when viewing other things before your competition begins.  It may cause it to not start up.
^T4View the top scores for this arena^BSHJumping Arena^R1

special_tiles.title: Gerbera's Flower Shop
special_tiles.description: A quaint little place on the edge of town owned by a quirky gal named Daisy. It is a small shop with a cute layout.  You walk up to the counter and it is lined with flowers. All of a sudden Daisy pops up from behind the counter and screams "Well, aren't you just precious!"  You start to blush but then you realize she is talking to a rose. Hmmm... this is interesting. You heard right about the quirky gal but she seems sweet.

special_tiles.title: Welcome to Christmas Isle!
special_tiles.description:
Sometimes there are presents hidden on Christmas Isle, but please take only one!
^X^Z

special_tiles.title: Welcome to Earton
special_tiles.description: Welcome traveler, we're all glad you're here! Lots going on today so please check out our town.^X^Z

special_tiles.title: Bee's Nest
special_tiles.description: There are lots of bees here! If you want though, you could try to take their honeycomb...^T4Steal Honeycomb from Bees^BMbees^R1

special_tiles.title: Barrel Racing
special_tiles.description:
Race around the barrels as fast as you can, but don't knock any of them down!
^T4View the best times for this game^BSTBarrel Racing^R1

special_tiles.title: Snowball Fight!
special_tiles.description: Bring it on, buddy! Let the snowballs fly here. Be careful not to hit each other in the face though.  That can really sting.

special_tiles.title: Welcome to Flipperton!
special_tiles.description:
Flipperton is a quiet retirement community.  You are welcome to visit the people of this town, as they rarely leave their quiet community and they do enjoy company.
^X^Z

special_tiles.title: Sara's Berry Patch
special_tiles.description: Please feel free to pick berries from my berry patch.  Don't eat too many or you might get a stomachache!

special_tiles.title: Sara's Cozy Cabin
special_tiles.description: Welcome to Sara's cabin.  Please come in for a cup of Earl Grey Tea and cuddle up in some quilts for a free nap!

special_tiles.title: Welcome to Englewilde
special_tiles.description: If you're looking for somewhere to stay, you've certainly stumbled upon the perfect place!^X^Z

special_tiles.title: Walden Pond
special_tiles.description: A peaceful pond that has plenty of fish.

special_tiles.title: Earton Inn
special_tiles.description: A tasty meal and a nice place to rest awaits the weary traveler who stops here.

special_tiles.title: Earton Inn
special_tiles.description: Basil Snoremore owns this inn and he is a perfectionist. He believes that the guest is the most important person so he pampers each and every one. You immediately sense this when you step in the door. Not a single swipe of dust to be found. Artwork is perfectly placed, not a single crumb on the tables, and the bathroom is spotless. How does he do this? It doesn't really matter though because for a little bit you get to live like a king or queen!

special_tiles.title: Walden Pond
special_tiles.description: A nice place to catch some fish or to just relax and enjoy the day.

special_tiles.title: Tiny Pond
special_tiles.description: There may be some fish here...

special_tiles.title: Tanagrama #3
special_tiles.description:
^T6Complete the Puzzle^BMtanagrama.swf?PUZZLE=7&QUEST=305&j=^R1
^X^Z

special_tiles.title: Checkers Room
special_tiles.description: There are checkerboards set up in here. You are invited to sit and play.

special_tiles.title: Earton Rock Shop
special_tiles.description: Brock is a great guy. As soon as you enter he's there to greet you and help you in finding the right rock. Mr. Limestone has a multitude of rocks and gems here and you wonder how far he has travelled to get them.

special_tiles.title: Earton Drawing Room
special_tiles.description:
In this cabin there is a giant easel with lots of pens. Everyone who enters is encouraged to go ahead and doodle alone or together.

DUE TO ABUSE - Only subscribers' drawings may be seen by other players.

special_tiles.title: Earton Wagon Station
special_tiles.description: Welcome to the Earton Wagon Station. There are three destinations to choose from. You can look at a map while you mull it over.

special_tiles.title: Earton Groomer
special_tiles.description: Phyllis is too busy to welcome you and people keep going in and out the door with their horses so she must be doing something right. You overhear her conversation with another customer and it seems like she does a great job. One person commented that it was as close to perfect as it could be. You can't help but notice that you are walking in about 4 inches of horse hair. She is either really busy with no time to sweep or she doesn't own a broom. She sees you observing the hair on the floor and winks.

special_tiles.title: Earton Horse Feed Store
special_tiles.description: On the door a sign reads "Mary Molasses, sweet as sugar."  Wow, the place is hopping. Customers are not only getting food for their horses but in the back of the store by the horsie treats stands Mary Molasses and she seems to be singing and whispering to the horses. The crowd is cheering her on. What is this all about? You are thinking about getting a closer look.

special_tiles.title: Earton Bank
special_tiles.description:
The bank is huge. Your voice echoes. You see a very short woman sitting behind a large columned counter made with some sort of stone. It's grand. There is not a soul around. Did you come in too early or too late? Why is no one here? You are a little nervous about putting your money in here. "Hello there, I am Penny. Can I help you?" Ah... um...
Note: A max of $9,999,999,999 is allowed to be held in the bank and a max of $2,147,483,647 on hand.

special_tiles.title: Martha and Hans' Cottage
special_tiles.description: Three little children run past you into the cottage, laughing and chasing each other. Over in one corner of the cozy dwelling sits a cheerful looking man reading a book, and to one side a plump, rosy-cheeked woman is baking. Checkered red curtains hang in the windows and a pretty vase of daisies, along with a teapot and some painted teacups, sit on the table. The woman turns to you and smiles pleasantly, wiping her floury hands on her apron.

special_tiles.title: Earton General Store
special_tiles.description: This is the perfect place to find everything you need.  No more running around town to get all your supplies.

special_tiles.title: Earton Direction Sign
special_tiles.description:
NORTH: Earton Jumping Arena
WEST: Boat Docks
EAST: Various Shops
SOUTH: Fishing Holes, Greater Horse Isle

special_tiles.title: Rider Isle Pond
special_tiles.description: A small, shallow pond.

special_tiles.title: Fishing Shop
special_tiles.description: Ernie is standing outside greeting his customers. He is a long legged man with lots of facial hair. He has a kind voice and appears to be doing a demonstration of some sort. You noticed a couple of ponds on the way to his store and it looks like customers are trying out equipment on those ponds. Ernie must be a really nice guy to do that. You walk in Mr. Angler's store and see that his equipment is top of the line. A customer nudges you, "Can you believe this fishing pole? And would you look at this price? It's our lucky day."

special_tiles.title: Fly N' Frog
special_tiles.description: Eat as many flies as possible... but don't fall in the water.^T5Fly N' Frog^BMflynfrog^R1^T4View the top scores for this game^BSHFly N Frog^R1^X^Z

special_tiles.title: Welcome to Horse Isle!
special_tiles.description: This is actually a small welcome island in the Secret Land of Horses! We recommend you explore this tiny island and go visit Welcome Willy in the cabin before venturing out into the rest of the world.  Use your arrow keys to move your character around this island.

special_tiles.title: Appleton Docks
special_tiles.description: Welcome to Appleton Docks.  You have a number of great destinations to choose from.

special_tiles.title: Shellton Docks
special_tiles.description: Welcome to Shellton Docks. If you choose to take a trip you will have a nice relaxing ride to your destination.

special_tiles.title: Treeton Docks
special_tiles.description: This dock doesn't offer much for options, but it may be better than trying to swim to your wanted destination.

special_tiles.title: Welcome Isle Boat Dock
special_tiles.description:
When you are ready to enter the world,  take this one-way boat trip.  Explore everything on this island before you leave however, because you can never return!
(and if you need money, go talk to Willy in the cabin)

special_tiles.title: Flipperton Docks
special_tiles.description: Welcome to Flipperton Docks. This deluxe boat offers a few destinations. The trip is spent traveling in luxury.

special_tiles.title: Snow Isle Docks
special_tiles.description: Welcome to Snow Isle Docks.  Caution:  Ice on dock, may be slippery.

special_tiles.title: Wington Docks
special_tiles.description: Welcome to Wington Docks. Conditions are breezy and warm today. Enjoy your trip.

special_tiles.title: Hotton Docks
special_tiles.description: Welcome to Hotton Docks. Caution: Low water levels. Please walk to far end of the dock to board your boat.

special_tiles.title: Earton Docks
special_tiles.description: Welcome to Earton Docks. Please be careful when boarding as the dock is a bit wobbly. You have many destinations to choose from.

special_tiles.title: Welcome to Horse Isle Seafarers
special_tiles.description:
Welcome to Earton, the northern town of Horse Isle.  If this is your first visit with us,  please visit our town center just east of here a bit.
^X^Z

special_tiles.title: Welcome Willy's Cabin
special_tiles.description: Welcome Willy would love to offer you a welcome to the land of Horse Isle.  Talk to him by clicking the Talk Button.  He is what we call a Non-Player-Character.  Willy and other NPC's can give you lots of helpful information, give you jobs, make deals with you, and send you on Quests!  It's wise to always talk to them when you find one.

special_tiles.title: Earton Wishing Well
special_tiles.description: A magical place for dropping wishing well coins!

special_tiles.title: Appleton Food Store
special_tiles.description: Located between the Inn and the Bank, this store has all you need. You see that samples are being given out and are wondering if you should have one.

special_tiles.title: Appleton Inn
special_tiles.description: It's not exactly what you had in mind for a rest but it will do the trick if you are really tired. You hear some giggles and screams. Hmm... Does Mr. Napper have kids?

special_tiles.title: Appleton Bank
special_tiles.description:
If you want to keep your money safe then this is the place. Good interest rates are paid also. Warren is eager to take your money.
Note: A max of $9,999,999,999 is allowed to be held in the bank and a max of $2,147,483,647 on hand.
Hovering over the ocean, you get the strange sensation you are falling, though your feet are steady over the water waves.  You feel the sea mist splash on your face as the waves seem to get higher.

special_tiles.title: Out Fishing
special_tiles.description: Busy little place with a wide assortment of fishing poles and tackle. You are not sure how you are supposed to find what you are looking for. Hopefully, Frank will help when  he comes back from fishing...

special_tiles.title: Speed Trainer
special_tiles.description: Here you can train your horse for speed improvements.

special_tiles.title: Bridge to Horseshoe Village on Hoof Isle
Hoof Isle Docks
special_tiles.description: Welcome to Hoof Isle Docks. Make sure you bring a hat or sunblock, it's going to be a sunny ride over to Turtle Isle.

special_tiles.title: Appleton Basket Shoot
special_tiles.description:
Two player challenge of throwing the ball into moving baskets.
^T4View the top scores for this game^BSWBasket Shoot^R1

special_tiles.title: Hoof Isle Direction Sign
special_tiles.description:
WEST: Horse Isle Mainland
EAST: Hoof Isle Boat Docks
SOUTH: Horseshoe Village
^X^Z
special_tiles.autoplay_swf: sign.swf?WEST=Horse Isle Mainland&EAST=Hoof Isle Boat Docks&SOUTH=Horseshoe Village&junk=

special_tiles.title: Horseshoe Rock Shop
special_tiles.description: The Rock Shop sits on the edge of Hoof Isle. Looks like it has a huge selection of rocks and gems. Sally is the owner and she seems a little rough around the edges. She's happy to help you if you ask nice but if not... well you were warned.

special_tiles.title: Henry Heimlich's Medical Station
special_tiles.description: Henry is the owner here and you believe that he is skilled and really does care about your horse. He smells of old spice. You can tell he is a hard worker by his energy  as he is running from exam room to exam room.

special_tiles.title: Flowers By Flo
special_tiles.description: The aroma in here is fantastic. Flo runs a cute and friendly flower shop. She's got all types of flowers.

special_tiles.title: Goodwin's Gear
special_tiles.description: Goodwin's Gear shop is located below the fishing shop. By the looks of it they cater to all of your needs.

special_tiles.title: Iona 's Cabin
special_tiles.description: Iona is the caretaker of the Flipperton Retirement community. Her cabin is actually rather messy.  She must devote all of her time to the community here.

special_tiles.title: Mr. Fin's Cabin
special_tiles.description:
Mr. Fin's cabin is filled with old sailing artifacts.  He even has his southern wall covered with old fish netting.  You notice several sailing books lining his mantle. He also has a painting easel setup, and is likely looking for someone to finish his painting for him.
^T6Paint Fin's Picture^BMpainting.swf?PAINTING=1&QUEST=127&j=^R1

special_tiles.title: Nolan's Cabin
special_tiles.description: Books are scattered everywhere in Nolan's cabin.  He must be an avid reader; but you wonder how he can actually find anything specific to read in this mess.

special_tiles.title: Flipperton General Store
special_tiles.description: Welcome to the Flipperton General Store. Trixie is a favorite among the Flipperton community. Her store is neatly arranged and she seems to have a lot of things that you like and just by looking at her you can tell she's friendly. Her store also has the wonderful aroma of fresh baked bread. Or is that coming from Helga's place? A sign on the door said that she gives out orange samples.

special_tiles.title: The Mare
special_tiles.description: The Mare Restaurant and Inn is a lovely place. There is a nice fireplace and banquet style tables. It smells like smoked fish. You see the daily menu states fresh fish caught locally.

special_tiles.title: Charlie Trimmer Grooming
special_tiles.description: Charlie Trimmer is the head groomer here and he gives you a lot of bangs for your buck! You can tell he clearly loves his job and the horses coming out of here look like prize winners.

special_tiles.title: Horseshoe Wishing Well
special_tiles.description: It's peaceful here. Take a break and wish for some good fortune.

special_tiles.title: La Fleur
special_tiles.description: The flower shop is charming with its cottage-like decor and beautifully displayed flowers.  Calla Lilly is standing behind the counter, looking as beautiful as the flowers she's surrounded by.

special_tiles.title: Mirah's Cabin
special_tiles.description: There are muddy footprints on the doormat, but the dirt stops there. The floors are worn from scrubbing and the walls could use another coat of paint, but the rest of the cabin is scrupulously clean. A pot of tea bubbles on the stove.^T6Paint Mirah's Picture^BMpainting.swf?PAINTING=11&QUEST=3440&j=^R1

special_tiles.title: Appleton Racing Arena
special_tiles.description:
Compete against others in this competition  that is mainly based off your horse's Speed and Endurance.  Only 6 horses can compete at one time.
Be careful when viewing other things before your competition begins.  It may cause your race to not start up.
^T4View the top scores for this Event^BSHRacing Arena^R1

special_tiles.title: Appleton Strength Trainer
special_tiles.description: You can put your horse in tip top shape here.

special_tiles.title: The Shore Rock Shop
special_tiles.description: A great place and it's on the beach! Come in and get a rock for your pocket.

special_tiles.title: The Hoof Isle General Store
special_tiles.description: You are greeted excitedly by Albert who claims he has unique items for sale. He is a portly man with lots of hair. His store is disorganized, and it's hard to tell if items are new or used.

special_tiles.title: Welcome to the North Pole!
special_tiles.description: Here you are at the North pole. You are one of the few lucky people to have a glimpse of what life with Santa is like. Have a look around and enjoy yourself!^X^Z

special_tiles.title: Marble Drop
special_tiles.description: In this park there is a challenging two player marble game setup. Find an opponent and go for it!

special_tiles.title: Welcome to Horseshoe Village!
special_tiles.description: Hello visitor and welcome! We hope you enjoy our kindly community. ^X^Z

special_tiles.title: Daisy Drop
special_tiles.description: The wind is blowing all of the daisies here into the air! Try and collect them if you want. ^T5 Daisy Drop ^BMdaiseydrop^R1^X^Z

special_tiles.title: Welcome to Shellton
special_tiles.description:
The beautiful town of Shellton welcomes you to enjoy its many parks and ponds.
^X^Z

special_tiles.title: Teepee Nap
special_tiles.description:
You can try napping in this teepee...  but it isn't easy!
^T5 Count Sheep ^BMcountsheep^R1^X^Z

special_tiles.title: Intersection of Green Avenue and Red Street
Intersection of Braeburn Avenue and Red Street
The Clip and Curl
special_tiles.description: You walk in and Claire is standing at the counter. She is on the phone and is describing her talents. "Honey, we do it all here. We can clip, cut, color, curl or braid your horsey's manes and tails." Wow, that seems good enough. You glance around and notice that her store is full. In the back you can see 2 horses getting washed and another one having a braid finished complete with a bow. Claire's store is very neat and respectable.

special_tiles.title: Shellton Vet
special_tiles.description: As soon as you walk in you are overwhelmed with an antiseptic smell. The receptionist is very friendly. Mathilda can fix your horse up in a jiffy and her rates are more than reasonable.

special_tiles.title: Chillton Wagon Station
special_tiles.description: Welcome to the Chillton Wagon Station. You can catch a ride to the Snow Isle Docks from here. There is no fireplace inside the station though so you will want to make a quick decision or you will be very cold.

special_tiles.title: Edelweiss Gazebo
special_tiles.description: You walk up the stairs of the gazebo and have a look around. It is very calming here. There is a slight breeze, you smell flowers and hear children playing at the park. Ahhh... this is the life.

special_tiles.title: Shellton Inn
special_tiles.description: "Welcome to the Shellton Inn where rest is our middle name" the sign reads. Upon entering a chubby cat runs up to you. As you reach down to pet it... he zooms away. The Inn is toasty warm and has a wonderful pine aroma.

special_tiles.title: Shellton Feed store
special_tiles.description: The store is well stocked and appears to be new. It has a fresh cut wood smell. Amelia is a pleasure to do business with. You overhear some customers commenting that she knows the products very well.

special_tiles.title: Ye Olde Blacksmithe
special_tiles.description: Good ole Earl Bronze. A town favorite for sure. The air is rather thick in here. Perhaps the fireplace is not venting properly. Mr. Bronze is always covered in soot. You see people gathered around Earl listening to another one of his stories. Shouldn't he be working? Although, you do see a stack of horseshoes waiting to be bought. Hmm... these people seem taken with his story, maybe you should check it out.

special_tiles.title: Shellton Tack Shop
special_tiles.description: You immediately notice that Lucy is distracted. She's running around the store with a broom. AHHH! You scream! A mouse runs over your foot and you jump. Feeling a little bit foolish, you realize that Lucy is chasing mice out of her store. She is afraid of them and has to remove them at once. She doesn't even notice that her customers have been waiting for her. You are wondering if you should help her so she can get back to her business.

special_tiles.title: Shellton Wishing Well
special_tiles.description: Make sure you stand close to the wishing well so your coins don't bounce off the sides when you toss them.

special_tiles.title: Jayne's House
special_tiles.description: You see Jayne's name on the door and are surprised to see a man inside.  He's sitting in the corner eating peaches out of a tin can with a simple metal fork.  On the wall is a blown-up photo of Jayne in what looks to be an orange and yellow knit hat with a red tassle on the top.  This couldn't be him, could it?

special_tiles.title: Shellton Poetry Room
special_tiles.description: Within this room hovers a peaceful poetic atmosphere.  It is suggested that minds can come together here and arrange words into simple harmony. Any thoughts remaining when you leave will be here for the next lucky visitor.

special_tiles.title: Rock Shoppe
special_tiles.description: The Shellton Rock Shoppe is located at the end of Padloper Boulevard. Upon entering you gather that it is a friendly little place. There is a wonderful beach smell in here and they have an amazing gem collection. You wonder if they have any rare gems?

special_tiles.title: Rachel's Boutique
special_tiles.description: Entering this clothes shop, you are impressed by the way everything is displayed so nicely. The owner Stella greets you and you can tell that by her own style she could help you dress to impress. She goes on to explain that it is their family's business and that they named it after their daughter Rachel.

special_tiles.title: Sierra's Cabin
special_tiles.description: You see a very cute baby sitting in a play pen.  You can hear Karina's mom, Sierra, busy in the kitchen and whatever she's cooking sure smells good.

special_tiles.title: Mr. Tuttle's Cabin
special_tiles.description:
Your nose begins to twitch as you step into the house. Is it the assortment of dried flowers that are hanging from the beams in the sitting room?  Oh wait, there must have been a cat here at one time.     Ka, Ka, ka, ka, CHeeeewwww!!!
^T6Paint Mr. Tuttle's Picture^BMpainting.swf?PAINTING=4&QUEST=147&j=^R1

special_tiles.title: Higgins' Cottage
special_tiles.description: You hear someone making weird noises inside.  "Aaaaeeeeiiiioooouuuuuyyyyy"

special_tiles.title: Veronica's Lodge
special_tiles.description:
There are toys everywhere and kids running around.  There is a general sense of chaos in this building.
^T6Play a song for Veronica's children^BMpianist.swf?TUNE=EDCEDCGFFEGFFEGPPBABPGGGPPBABPGGFEDC&QUEST=190&j=^R1

special_tiles.title: Shellton General Store
special_tiles.description: There is a wood carved owl standing outside the store that has the following message on it. "This is your average general store. We've probably got what you need and if not try somewhere else." Hmm... not exactly friendly but this explains a lot when you see Phoebe. She doesn't really fit in too well with the community. She is a bit of a tomboy and has some sort of lumberjack outfit on and is sporting a very grumpy face. Do you dare talk to her?

special_tiles.title: Intersection of Carapace Lane and Box Avenue
Intersection of Box Avenue and Spiny Street
Intersection of Carapace Lane and Painted Avenue
Intersection of Snapping Street and Marine Avenue
Intersection of Speckled Street and Galapagos Ave
Intersection of Speckled Street and Marine Avenue
Intersection of Painted Ave and Leatherback Lane
Intersection of Leatherback Lane and Galapagos Ave
Intersection of Fuji St and Golden Delicious Ln
Intersection of Fuji St and Golden Delicious Ln
Intersection of Braeburn Avenue and Fuji Street
Intersection of Green Ave and Fuji Street
Band Hall
special_tiles.description: Come join with others and make music here.

special_tiles.title: Treeton Dressage Arena
special_tiles.description:
Compete against others in this competition  that is mainly based off your horse's conformation and groom.  Only 5 horses can compete at one time.
Be careful when viewing other things before your competition begins.  It may cause it to not start up.
^T4View the top scores for this arena^BSHDressage Arena^R1

special_tiles.title: Santa's Workshop
special_tiles.description: Ha! You've heard kids and grownups say that Santa wasn't real! But look! Here he is! Mrs. Claus looks to be baking cookies,  while Mr. Claus is sitting with a very ponderous look. Elves are busy wrapping presents here, they offer to wrap some for you too!

special_tiles.title: Woods Cabin
special_tiles.description:
This old simple rickety cabin has been vacant for quite some time. There is a faded note on the table and you can make out most of the letters...

'Welc-me Vis-t-r. I hav- go-e in se-r-h of a Ma-ic-l Un--o-n I saw in t-e n--rby gl-d-! I kno- The-e h-s to b- so-e w-y p--t th- Ol- De-d T--e, I Just need to look Cl--e Eno--h!!!'

Well.. Without being able to understand that note. . This whole trip is probably pointless!

special_tiles.title: Snow Isle Wagon Station
special_tiles.description: Welcome to the Snow Isle Wagon Station. You have 2 destination choices here and they are both great if you want to go somewhere cold.

special_tiles.title: Elf's Cabin
special_tiles.description: You hurry inside a small red cabin to get out of the cold for a while.  Looking around you are amazed at all the toys piled everywhere.  In the middle of a stack of wooden trains you see an elf.  Looking closer you see he has a slingshot and he's aiming it right at your head!  Ducking down you hear a whizzing over your head and a "splat" as something hits the door behind you.  Turning around you see the remains of a plastered snowball slowly melting and sliding down the door.

special_tiles.title: Northernmost Point of Horse Isle
special_tiles.description: You have reached the northernmost point of horse isle. Good Job! Unfortunately, there are no rewards for doing this. You might want to walk around a bit though before you leave.

special_tiles.title: Eliza's Cabin
special_tiles.description: This cabin is very humid, there are half a dozen washtubs full of warm water almost overflowing with bubbles.  There are piles of neatly folded laundry on a table by the door.

special_tiles.title: Welcome to Chillton
special_tiles.description: Brrr... welcome to the land of snow! Have yourself a nice brisk walk and stop at a cabin or two for a warm up and some tasty cocoa.

special_tiles.title: Christmas Isle Wagon Station
special_tiles.description: Welcome to Christmas Isle Wagon Station. There is only one route available from here and you've heard Snow Isle is nice.

special_tiles.title: Agility Trainer
special_tiles.description: Your horse might be in need of some training. It's a little spendy but you've heard it's worth it.

special_tiles.title: The Rod and Reel
special_tiles.description: This fishing shop has the latest and greatest in fishing equipment and some pretty fabulous fish to boot.

special_tiles.title: Treeton Hometown Foods
special_tiles.description: You notice a sign 'From our place to yours, we take care of all your baking and cooking needs'.  Minnie is known all around Horse Isle for being generous with samples and for having high quality products.

special_tiles.title: Treeton Farrier
special_tiles.description: Wow, it is really hot and smokey in here. Lars must be working hard right now. You can almost taste the metal in your mouth. You knock louder but being that Lars is hard of hearing from years of pounding it could take him a bit.

special_tiles.title: Treeton Farrier
special_tiles.description: Wonderful craftsmanship can be found here.

special_tiles.title: Treeton Vet
special_tiles.description: From what you've heard, it's all in her name.  Only Nora can nurture your horse back to health.

special_tiles.title: Treeton Gear Shop
special_tiles.description: Your basic run of the mill gear shop.  Nothing special but Vicky stands by her equipment, so you won't be let down either.

special_tiles.title: Treeton Feed Shop
special_tiles.description: Oliver is always willing to help. He enjoys talking with his customers. Sometimes for hours...

special_tiles.title: Treeton General Store
special_tiles.description: Just like the other general stores, this one has been stocked well and we have Sasha to thank for that. She is a nice gal and quite a talker.

special_tiles.title: Treeton Flower Shop
special_tiles.description: You need flowers? Well, then you've come to the right place. Helena will be happy to help you.

special_tiles.title: Treeton Inn
special_tiles.description: Are you feeling a little sleep deprived? This is the place for you. Cecil will take good care of you. A good night's sleep is a must before any big competition.

special_tiles.title: Out of the Closet
special_tiles.description: Max always says "If your jeans have holes in them or your favorite hat was taken by the wind on your last ride then you've come to the right place."  They have all the latest in riding apparel for sale here.

special_tiles.title: Treeton Rock Shop
special_tiles.description: This is no ordinary rock shop. Have you heard about the owner? Mr. Pebbleton is a little on the kooky side and you just never know what he will try to sell you.

special_tiles.title: Igloo at the Top of the World
special_tiles.description: Sera is dressed in a fur lined parka.  All around you see polar fleece blankets, down comforters and pillows. On the small stove is a steaming pot of hot cocoa.

special_tiles.title: Elf's Cabin
special_tiles.description: You've found one of Santa's Elves! Although there are a lot of them up here at the North Pole most are busy in Santa's workshop.  Jilly Elf is busy working on the newest toy for next year, a western cowgirl doll.  She looks up as you enter and smiles.

special_tiles.title: Snowy Sleigh Ride
special_tiles.description:
Sleigh Ride^T6Guide the sleigh down the pass as fast as you can!^BMsleighride.swf?^R1
^T4View the top scores for this game^BSHSleigh Ride^R1
^X^Z

special_tiles.title: Shellton Fountain
special_tiles.description: Fresh, cool water from the fountain.

special_tiles.title: Construction Job
special_tiles.description:
There is a construction site here.  If you wanted to help them assemble wooden panels, they will pay you!^T6Easy Job^BMpuzzle1.swf?LEVEL=EASY&j=^R1^T6Medium Job^BMpuzzle1.swf?LEVEL=MEDIUM&j=^R1^T6Hard Job^BMpuzzle1.swf?LEVEL=HARD&j=^R1
^T4View the top scores for this game^BSHConstruction Job^R1^X^Z

special_tiles.title: Christmas Isle Pond
special_tiles.description: Welcome to Christmas Isle Pond. You can fish, skate or walk on it but please be careful for thin ice during the early spring and fall seasons.

special_tiles.title: Christmas Isle Pond
special_tiles.description: Welcome to Christmas Isle Pond. Catch yourself some fish and don't slip.

special_tiles.title: Pyramid #1
special_tiles.description:
If you wish, you could explore the Labyrinth within this pyramid!
^T6Explore Pyramid^BMpyramidmaze.swf?MAZE=1&QUEST=23&j=^R1
^X^Z

special_tiles.title: Santon Wagon Station
special_tiles.description: You stumble upon the wagon station. There are benches inside but barely visible due to the amount of sand on them. There is a board with destinations and prices but it's a little hard to see because of the dust blowing up from all the sound.

special_tiles.title: Welcome to Santon
special_tiles.description: Welcome to the land of sand. Please make yourself at home here and don't be surprised if you have sand in your food and drink.^X^Z

special_tiles.title: Santon Wishing Well
special_tiles.description: The wishing well is the center of Santon. All those who toss a few coins in walk away feeling good.

special_tiles.title: Bena Buket's General Store
special_tiles.description: If you are in need of the basics, well then you've come to the right place, and just so you know everything has sand in it or on it so don't bother complaining to Bena about it.

special_tiles.title: Hotton Wagon Station
special_tiles.description: Welcome to the Wagon Station in Hotton. You glance around and see that Santon seems to be the only destination. There are also barrels with numerous coconuts in them. You try to think of all the reason for that but have not come up with a good one yet. It is also difficult to think when you are sweating so profusely from the heat here.

special_tiles.title: Welcome to Hotton
special_tiles.description: Glad you made it through the desert to our town. You're welcome to stay as long as you can tolerate the heat.^X^Z

special_tiles.title: Dakota's Home
special_tiles.description: Hello? Anybody there? It's dark in here and you can't see a thing. It seems like nobody is home. Hmm... oh wait. You see a note lying on the table, it reads "Looking for scorpions, be back shortly." That's interesting.

special_tiles.title: Wynona's Home
special_tiles.description: Wynona is famous for her cactus dishes. The town is always talking about what she's going to make next. She has cactus in every square inch of her cabin and if it's not the real deal then it is a decoration. She is even wearing clothing with cacti on it. She motions for you to sit down and starts telling you all the uses of cacti.

special_tiles.title: Pillan's Home
special_tiles.description: Pillan's home is very well lit.  What a difference from Dakota's home. Although, it's so bright in here it's a little hard to focus. He is a lean man with hard features. He is leaning over his stove cooking a big pot of soup and it smells delicious! His three children are playing some sort of games with rocks. The children tell you that their mom is out by the wishing well.

special_tiles.title: Kele's Home
special_tiles.description: Kele lives with her dad and pet buzzard Mooki. You are a bit frightened of the buzzard who is staring at you like a guard dog. However, Kele assures you he is gentle. She explains to you that Mooki flys all the way to Shellton to deliver messages to her friend. You find this fascinating and would secretly like to try it.

special_tiles.title: Fala's Home
special_tiles.description:
Hmm... Fala's door is rather small so you have to duck down to get in. She has incense burning that smells like very strong perfume. You are not sure how long you will be able to stay in here. She has no furniture and you are pretty sure she sleeps on the floor.
^T6Paint Fala's Picture^BMpainting.swf?PAINTING=8&QUEST=151&j=^R1

special_tiles.title: Pyramid #2
special_tiles.description:
If you wish, you could explore the Labyrinth within this pyramid!
^T6Explore Pyramid^BMpyramidmaze.swf?MAZE=2&QUEST=47&j=^R1
^X^Z

special_tiles.title: Oasis
special_tiles.description: Yes, this is an oasis and you can even catch fish from it. Go ahead and give it a whirl.

special_tiles.title: Oasis
special_tiles.description: Feeling a little hot? Go ahead and dip your toes in or catch a few fish. It also happens to be one of the prettiest places around here to just relax at.

special_tiles.title: Leroy's Cabin
special_tiles.description: You push open the door after knocking several times. You are pretty sure you just heard something growl. All of a sudden Leroy jumps out of the darkness with a bearskin on his back. You are terribly frightened! Leroy begins to laugh and tell you it's just him and not to be afraid. He seems to be a bit of a prankster. You wish you could see the rest of his cabin but it's dark and he refuses to turn any lights on.

special_tiles.title: Direction Sign
special_tiles.description:
NORTH: Hotton West across Desert
EAST: Santon Northerly in Middle of Desert
WEST: Vast Desert
^X^Z
special_tiles.autoplay_swf: sign.swf?NORTH=Hotton, west across desert&WEST=Vast Desert&EAST=Santon, north in middle of desert&junk=

special_tiles.title: Tiny Pond
special_tiles.description: There may be some fish here... hope you brought your fishing pole with today.

special_tiles.title: Moody, Moody Horses
special_tiles.description: These horses are very moody!  Try your best to make them all happy.^T6Easy^BMmoodyhorses.swf?LEVEL=EASY&j=^R1^T6Medium^BMmoodyhorses.swf?LEVEL=MEDIUM&j=^R1^T6Hard^BMmoodyhorses.swf?LEVEL=HARD&j=^R1^X^Z

special_tiles.title: Pond
special_tiles.description: The fish are jumping today!

special_tiles.title: Pond
special_tiles.description: The fish are jumping today!

special_tiles.title: Galvin's Cabin
special_tiles.description: Galvin's cabin is a small little place  with lots of books about travel on his shelves.

special_tiles.title: Galvin's Island Cabin
special_tiles.description: A run down, dilapidated building sits around you.  You are actually worried it might collapse on you!

special_tiles.title: Galvin's Pond
special_tiles.description: Bet you didn't think there would be a pond on this little island. But Galvin needs to eat something and he can't be eating Dolphins and certainly can't survive on just coconuts. Feel free to catch some fish or just replenish your horse's water supply.

special_tiles.title: Quiet Isle Boat Dock
special_tiles.description: A tiny, private dock, there are just a couple nice boats around and no crowds.

special_tiles.title: Quiet Isle Pond
special_tiles.description: Welcome to Quiet Isle Pond. Catch some fish while you are here but please keep the enthusiasm down. Your tone of voice must not rise above normal.

special_tiles.title: Rafiki's Cabin
special_tiles.description:
It looks like Rafiki has been gone for a while. Cobwebs have secured themselves in the corners of this small, dark cabin. Upon looking around you find a note:
Dear Mum,
If you come looking for me, I am hiding in the forest on this island. I heard there was a stranger wandering about so I figured I would hide until they are gone. I would hate to give away any secrets...
Bye Mum!
- Rafiki

special_tiles.title: Venda's Cabin
special_tiles.description: Venda's large cabin is very clean and neat.  You can tell she doesn't appreciate disorder.

special_tiles.title: Felton's Cabin
special_tiles.description: Upon entering Felton's cabin you immediately notice a thin layer of dust covering the table and floor below it.  Upon staring at it, he says "bone dust".  Upon noticing this does not comfort you at all he explains further, "I study dinosaur bones!"

special_tiles.title: Waverly's Cabin
special_tiles.description: Waverly is doing crossword puzzles and frequently gets together with neighbors to play bridge. You notice he has many tools and gadgets around the cabin. He is the handyman in the community.

special_tiles.title: Sandra's Cabin
special_tiles.description:
As you enter you notice a lot of pastel furniture and linens.  There are jars and berries everywhere.  Sandra is bustling around her kitchen.  Her cabin is incredibly clean for how much work it appears she puts into making jams with all those berries.
^T6Play a song for Sandra^BMpianist.swf?TUNE=CCDCDEDEFEFGFGAGABABPGEC&QUEST=448&j=^R1

special_tiles.title: Helga's Cabin
special_tiles.description: Before you even get inside you smell fresh bread baking. The cabin is large with many windows. You open the door and see that Helga is wearing a long flower print dress and her long gray hair is wrapped neatly into a bun. You have heard that she wears a dress everyday and keeps her hair the same way too. She has lots of beautiful swedish painted horses everywhere. All of her furniture is made out of wood and she is preparing tea on the stove.

special_tiles.title: Heinrich's Cabin
special_tiles.description:
You push the door open, and the air feels just as cold inside as outside.  There is no fire going.  There must not be anyone here, you think.  Then you hear a deep voice say, "Hello there.  Make yourself at home."  It sounds like a nice invitation, but you are so cold.  Mr. Heinrich, a lonely man, calls out again.  "I don't like fires.  I like to be cold.  Toughens a person up.  I do drink hot beverages though.  Clears out the nose."
^T6Play a song for Heinrich^BMpianist.swf?TUNE=GEDCDEGEDCDEGEGAEAGEDC&QUEST=450&j=^R1
The north wall of the maze here has a mark on it.

special_tiles.title: Valarie's Cabin
special_tiles.description:
You walk up to the door and Valarie greets you before you can knock.  She's eager for visitors.  She always has a plate of cookies and milk out in the hopes that Santa will make an unscheduled stop.  That's right, Santa.  Right now you are thinking she is a bit bananas.  You are not the only one.
^T6Paint Valarie's Picture^BMpainting.swf?PAINTING=3&QUEST=145&j=^R1

special_tiles.title: Abigail's Cabin
special_tiles.description: Meet Abigail.  She used to live in Santon but couldn't take the heat so she made a major climate move. The community loves her. She's the talk of the town with her witty remarks and beautiful looks. Her cabin smells of lavender and wood smoke. An interesting combination. Her favorite things are: building snow forts, ice skating, hearing her feet crunch in the snow, and enjoying cocoa by the fireplace.

special_tiles.title: Cedric's Cabin
special_tiles.description: Cedric maintains the town's wood supply.  He is handy with an axe and is always looking to store up the town's heating reserves.  Up here, firewood is as good as gold!  On his walls Cedric has many old pairs of snowshoes decorating his walls.  They give it a very adventurous look, but you guess that Cedric is the kind of guy that has actually used them.  They're not just for decoration!

special_tiles.title: Nicolette's Cabin
special_tiles.description:
This cabin is empty, but still very warm. You notice a note on the Table:
I went for a short walk outside. I should be back soon.
-Nicolette
One wonders why anyone would go outside on a chilly day like today when they have such a warm cabin...

special_tiles.title: Rupert's Cabin
special_tiles.description: Rupert and his small pony 'Chilly' live here.  You can not believe he actually lives with his horse!  The walls are bare.  One could imagine they would have to be with a tail whipping around.  The floor is covered in straw.  Chilly is hunched over by the fire, along with Rupert in an old chair, both of them staring endlessly into the warm flames.  Upon Rupert getting up and opening the door for you, Chilly pushes through for some exercise outside.

special_tiles.title: Ryland's Cabin
special_tiles.description: Ryland's cabin is very spacious.  He appears to be an avid hunter.  Several stuffed specimens cover his walls.  He also has several life-like paintings of ducks covering the walls.

special_tiles.title: Dalton's Cabin
special_tiles.description: Old man Dalton and his grandson share this old cabin.  Neither of them can work, so they are short on money.  You can tell by the looks of them that they don't quite get enough to eat, still they look to be very happy.

special_tiles.title: Larissa's Cabin
special_tiles.description: Upon entering you notice everything is pink. The walls, the curtains, the floor, the linens, etc. There are knick knacks everywhere and there is not a wall left bare. You can't help but feel overwhelmed by her girly ways.

special_tiles.title: Parry's Cabin
special_tiles.description: Parry is a simple man and his cabin reflects that. If it doesn't serve a purpose Parry doesn't want it.

special_tiles.title: Yancy's Cabin
special_tiles.description:
Looking around Yancy's place makes you feel all warm and fuzzy inside. You enjoy the scent of freshly baked cookies and the friendly smile that Yancy gives you.
^T6Play a song for Yancy^BMpianist.swf?TUNE=CCGGAAGFFEEDDCGGFFEEDGGFFEEDCCGGAAGFFEEDDC&QUEST=189&j=^R1

special_tiles.title: Vianca's Cabin
special_tiles.description:
Upon knocking on the door, Vianca bursts it open.  With her chipmunk like quick-fidgiting she makes you mildly uneasy.  Inside you see one of the cleanest cabins on Horse Isle.   In fact you search your entire field of vision for a single fuzz or speck...  Upon thinking you see one, Vianca notices your glance and zips over brushing it up in a split second.  She is really tiring to watch.
^T6Paint Vianca's Picture^BMpainting.swf?PAINTING=7&QUEST=152&j=^R1

special_tiles.title: Octavio's Cabin
special_tiles.description: Upon entering Octavio's cabin you notice several paintings of...  Vianca, his southernly neighbor! His cabin is a complete mess.  Scraps of crumpled notes overfill his garbage pail and what looks like biscuit crumbs are all over the floor.

special_tiles.title: Jaelyn's Cabin
special_tiles.description: Looking around you notice that everything is rather dusty. It appears as though Jaelyn is not around much. The rumor is that she is a bit of a traveler. Hmm, wonder if the suitcase by the door means she is about to go on a trip?

special_tiles.title: Joylyn's Cabin
special_tiles.description: You jump back at the amount of grasshoppers that are surrounding you. Glancing at the table you notice a book with a mention of entomology and realize it's going to be okay.  Joylyn studies bugs. Whew. For a minute you were terrified.

special_tiles.title: Barnabas and Caelin's Cabin
special_tiles.description:
Barnabas and Caelin's cabin is rather cramped. They are large people with lots of large things.  Some of which includes a wall full of large books that appear to contain a lot of information.  The majority, on horses.  You wonder how they can handle it. If you were claustrophobic you would need to leave.
^T6Help Barnabas with his cookie cutter^BMcookiecutter.swf?COOKIE=0&QUEST=1302&j=^R1

special_tiles.title: Cabin of Carter & Magnolia
special_tiles.description: Magnolia, along with her husband and baby girl, live here.  It appears all they do is fuss over their sweet newborn. They seem truly happy.

special_tiles.title: Temperance's Cabin
special_tiles.description: Mayor Temperance's Cabin sits in the northernmost portion of Treeton.  She takes pride in the clock-work like efficiency of her town.  She has been Mayor now for over 10 years.  While streaks of gray hair have begun,  her ever-smiling face makes her look younger.

special_tiles.title: Sabella's Cabin
special_tiles.description: Sabella takes full advantage of the wonderful apples her community grows.  You can see she has several apple pies cooling, many jars of applesauce, and baskets full of more apples just waiting to be prepared.  She even has an apple design on her apron.  Over the mantle, above some drying apple slices, she has a painting of her favorite horse breed,  the Appaloosa!  You cannot help but imagine why.

special_tiles.title: Inara's Cabin
special_tiles.description:
Inara is known around Horse Isle as one of the most beautiful people.  She has not let it go to her head, however.  She will sit and visit with any travelers that stop by.  After welcoming you in she immediately puts the kettle on and will offer you a choice of warm beverages. 
^T6Play a song for Inara^BMpianist.swf?TUNE=EEFGGFEDCCDEEDDEEFGGFEDCCDEDCC&QUEST=191&j=^R1

special_tiles.title: Bruno and Ursala's Cabin
special_tiles.description: Ursala and her husband Bruno have been living here for years. They own all the apple trees you see in town. Don't let Sabella fool you with her love of apples. She pretends to be the queen of apples but the clear winner here is Ursala. After all, they give the fruit life. Needless to say this is why everything in their cabin is apple related. Ursala is in the kitchen right now cooking up some sort of apple dish (everything she cooks has apple in it somewhere). ^T6Help Ursala with her cookie cutter^BMcookiecutter.swf?COOKIE=1&QUEST=1307&j=^R1

special_tiles.title: Kaliska's Cabin
special_tiles.description:
What kind of name is Kaliska? Well have you been to Chillton yet? Kaliska is a sweet old lady who will be happy to tell you all about her heritage. Like her, the cabin is full of life and her heirlooms are all over.
^T6Paint Kaliska's Picture^BMpainting.swf?PAINTING=9&QUEST=146&j=^R1

special_tiles.title: Reuben's Cabin
special_tiles.description: Wow, this place is funky looking. There are bright colors all over, balloon animals hanging from the ceiling and strange horns. Apparently, Reuben is the town clown and entertains families on the weekends by the fountain. His dream is to be a rodeo clown. You wish you could try on his clown shoes.

special_tiles.title: Adrianna and Hershel's Cabin
special_tiles.description: Adrianna and her husband have a wonderful steed 'WildFire' that is said to be so intelligent that it can understand human speech! When you walk into the cabin, you are greeted by pictures of Wildfire and the warm smell of leather. Looking around, you see a small workbench over in the corner.

special_tiles.title: Faustus' Cabin
special_tiles.description: Faustus enjoys his peace and quiet.  It's why he built his rickety shack in these woods.  Unfortunately, Appleton has grown since then, and has started to encroach into his 'personal space.'  He has heard rumors of an island called 'Quiet Isle,' and he is dreaming of someday being able to move there.

special_tiles.title: Wington Pond
special_tiles.description: You've entered Wington Pond. Soak up the sun and beautiful flowers surrounding you. Oh yeah, and you can catch some fish or give your horse some water while you are relaxing.

special_tiles.title: Welcome to Wington
special_tiles.description: Welcome to Wington! Our beautiful town is found on the historic Bird Isle.^X^Z

special_tiles.title: Wington Fountain
special_tiles.description: Before you stands a Wington gathering place, the lovely Wington Fountain.  Its pristine waters are continually replenished by the natural underground spring below it.

special_tiles.title: Wington Bank
special_tiles.description:
The architecture in this building is incredible and you wish you had your camera with. Oh well, you are here to conduct business anyway. Mr. Funds will be happy to assist you.
Note: A max of $9,999,999,999 is allowed to be held in the bank and a max of $2,147,483,647 on hand.

special_tiles.title: Cabin of Rolando & Yolanda
special_tiles.description:
As you enter the cabin, you see a very happy Yolanda knitting a pair of little booties. Rolando is at her side, attendant to any and all her needs. You glance over at the corner of the room and see a bassinet and other baby things. How sweet!
^T6Help Rolando with his cookie cutter^BMcookiecutter.swf?COOKIE=2&QUEST=1309&j=^R1

special_tiles.title: Abril's Cabin
special_tiles.description: You are welcomed at the door by Abril. Walking into his cabin you see that it is filled with anything and everything that has to do with horses.

special_tiles.title: Direction Sign
special_tiles.description:
WEST: Hotton
EAST: Santon
^X^Z

special_tiles.title: Isadora's Cabin
special_tiles.description:
Do you smell that? It's the sweet, salty, fresh smell of the ocean. Isadora is living in paradise. She loves it here and her place shows it. You see sand in bottles, driftwood sculptures and rock art all over. She also has some great island music playing. You could hang out here all day.
^T6Paint Isadora's Picture^BMpainting.swf?PAINTING=5&QUEST=148&j=^R1

special_tiles.title: Deidra's Cabin
special_tiles.description: Deidra's cabin has a wonderful view of the Eastern Seas surrounding Horse Isle. She spends much of her time combing the sand beaches looking for natural treasures which have washed themselves ashore.

special_tiles.title: Wington Rocks
special_tiles.description: This rock shop is a great little place on the edge of town that displays a sign reading "You got money, we got rocks."  Nothing could be more blunt.

special_tiles.title: Dominique's Cabin
special_tiles.description: Dominique is a young mother of a small child.  Her house is in slight disarray, babyclothes there, toys here, but no more than can be expected.  A picture of her favorite horse 'Nebula' hangs above the fireplace.

special_tiles.title: Zamora's Cabin
special_tiles.description: Zamora is not very approachable nor is her cabin. She doesn't talk much and when she does she is usually sarcastic and sometimes just plain old rude. She moved here from Santon and is a bit of a loner. Even her cabin is cold and unfriendly. She is a bit crazy and the locals don't appreciate her antics.

special_tiles.title: Wington Feed and Seed
special_tiles.description: Mr. Shoogerkube does not like your horse sampling his feed and is not much for chit chat.

special_tiles.title: Hannah's Cabin
special_tiles.description:
Meet Hannah, a delightful young girl living with her mother Zachava. You sense that she is a little shy and you are right. She collects four leaf clovers. If you have any, chances are she'd she be very glad to have them. She might even be more talkative!
^T6Paint Hannah's Picture^BMpainting.swf?PAINTING=6&QUEST=149&j=^R1
Sitting here in remarkably luxurious enclosures, you see some equally remarkable animals--and an ordinary till!

special_tiles.title: Gertrude's Cabin
special_tiles.description: Gertrude is a gabby gal with some spunk. You immediately sense this as you enter her cabin and see her chatting and laughing loudly with the neighbor. She appears to be a much better talker than cleaner. Her cabin smells a bit musty and there are dirty dishes scattered about.

special_tiles.title: Patience's Cabin
special_tiles.description: Her name says a lot here. Her cabin is quiet; you haven't heard a peep. She is rocking in her chair and it looks as though she has been there for days waiting for someone to visit. When she sees you enter she jumps from her chair at you and almost knocks you to the ground.

special_tiles.title: Wington Tack Supply
special_tiles.description: One would say that Tessa's store is a little run down but when you look around you realize that it just has a lot of character.

special_tiles.title: Elaina's Cabin
special_tiles.description:
Ooh, it's nice and toasty warm in here. Elaina smiles sweetly at you and you look around for milk and cookies because you are certain there must be some.
^T6Play the piano for Elaina^BMpianist.swf?TUNE=EDCDEEEDDDEGGEDCDEEEEDDEDC&QUEST=187&j=^R1

special_tiles.title: Direction Sign
special_tiles.description:
NORTH: Business District
SOUTH: Residential District
^X^Z

special_tiles.title: The Colt of Wington
special_tiles.description: The Colt of Wington is a cozy place where you can hang your hat and almost call it home. You never know what William might say and by the looks of this place you are pretty sure that relaxation and good food are in order.

special_tiles.title: Wington Blacksmith
special_tiles.description: This is a great place to get some horseshoes if you can get Liam to talk with you. As you enter this fine establishment, you hear the floorboards creaking and an old man named Liam grumpily shouts "Who's there?"  You are not sure whether you should answer or walk back out and get your horseshoes another day. Either way Liam will be there and always answers his door the same way.

special_tiles.title: Gone Fishin'
special_tiles.description: Hmm.... from the smell in here you are guessing that not only do they sell fishing equipment but also fish.

special_tiles.title: Roses are Red
special_tiles.description: Like the name, it screams poetry in this place. Everything is perfectly placed, flowers are creatively arranged and even Iris is oozing with charm.

special_tiles.title: Wington Clothing
special_tiles.description: Clothing galore! Betty really has everything packed in here. What is she thinking? Word has it she's more about the money than the customer service.

special_tiles.title: Sandcastle Moat #2
special_tiles.description:
^T6Straighten out the Moat^BMsandcastlemoat.swf?BOARD=2&QUEST=323&j=^R1
^X^Z

special_tiles.title: Ice Sculpture #1
special_tiles.description:
^T6Chip out the Ice Sculpture^BMicesculpture.swf?BOARD=1&QUEST=354&j=^R1

^X^Z

special_tiles.title: Community Vegetable Garden
special_tiles.description: What a lovely vegetable garden. A sign reads: Please check with Zachava before picking any produce. Volunteers always welcome.

special_tiles.title: Cadence's Vegetable Garden
special_tiles.description: You are welcome to tend this garden... It only produces veggies when kept weed free.^T6Weed the Garden!^BMweeding^R1^X^Z

Intersection of Oak Ring Road and Spruce Branch Road
Intersection of Maple Ring Road and Linden Branch
Intersection of Maple Ring Road and Linden Branch
Intersection of Maple Ring Road and Spruce Branch Road
Intersection of Maple Ring Road and Spruce Branch Road
Intersection of Feather Way Road and Migration Street
Appleton Blacksmith
special_tiles.description: Arthur the Appleton Blacksmith is proud of his shop and of his craft. He is happy to sell you any size and style of horseshoe that you want. If he doesn't have what you need in stock, he'll make it while you wait.

special_tiles.title: Appleton Fountain
special_tiles.description: Looking at the beautiful fountain and flowers that surround it you might think you are in paradise.

special_tiles.title: Ant Hill #1
special_tiles.description:
If you wish,  you could help the Ant within this Ant Hill store his food!
^T6Help in Ant Hill #1^BManthillz.swf?HILL=1&QUEST=51&j=^R1
^T4View the top scores for this game^BSHAntHill #1^R1
^X^Z

special_tiles.title: Horseshoe Wagon Station
special_tiles.description: Sitting near the beach, this very small wagon station only goes one place.  Appleton.
