special_tiles.title: Earton Poetry Room
special_tiles.description: Within this room hovers a peaceful poetic atmosphere.  It is suggested that minds can come together in here and arrange words into simple harmony.  Any thoughts remaining when you leave will remain intact for the next lucky visitor.

special_tiles.title: Chess Clubhouse
special_tiles.description: There are a bunch of Chessboards setup on tables in here and you are welcomed to sit down and play with another player.

special_tiles.title: Freddy's Home
special_tiles.description: Inside this raised house you find a small man and a very large dog.^T6Paint Freddy's Picture^BMpainting.swf?PAINTING=12&QUEST=3442&j=^R1

special_tiles.title: Wington Drawing Room
special_tiles.description:
In this cabin there is a giant easel with lots of pens. Everyone who enters is encouraged to go ahead and doodle alone or together.

DUE TO ABUSE - Only subscribers' drawings may be seen by other players.

special_tiles.title: Wington Poetry Room
special_tiles.description: Within this room hovers a peaceful poetic atmosphere.  It is suggested that minds can come together in here and arrange words into simple harmony. Any thoughts remaining when you leave will remain intact for the next lucky visitor.

special_tiles.title: Treasure Hunter
special_tiles.description: The winner of this 2 player game earns $100!

special_tiles.title: Charla Mae's Home
special_tiles.description: All you smell is citrus as you walk in.  Charla Mae is in the next room surrounded by oranges.

special_tiles.title: Hotton Bank
special_tiles.description:
Wesley and Harold offer you a wide variety of banking options. You observe that Wesley does all the talking and Harold keeps quiet. Harold will whisper at Wesley and then Wesley speaks. What is the story with that? You are very curious now.
Note: A max of $9,999,999,999 is allowed to be held in the bank and a max of $2,147,483,647 on hand.

special_tiles.title: Bee's Nest
special_tiles.description: There are lots of bees here!  If you want though, you could try to take their honeycomb...^T4Steal Honeycomb from Bees^BMbees.swf?m=^R1

special_tiles.title: Karina's Boutique
special_tiles.description: Well, this place is a bit on the small side but Karina has found a way to pack it full. Is that Karina behind the counter? Whoever it is she can't seem to get off the phone to help you or stop snapping her gum.

special_tiles.title: Hotton Feed Store
special_tiles.description: Greetings from Luke as you walk in the door. He's a friendly fellow with lots of charm. Mr. Straw's store is a little messy but he certainly makes up for it with his stellar sales pitch. He starts talking and folks start throwing money at him. You wonder if he has any job openings.

special_tiles.title: Hotton Endurance Trainer
special_tiles.description: Here your horse will be trained by professionals.

special_tiles.title: Dixie's Cabin
special_tiles.description:
Dixie is in the kitchen with an orange stained apron on. The sweet smell of citrus fills the room and there are orange rinds everywhere.
^T6Play a song for Dixie^BMpianist.swf?TUNE=CEDFEGFAGBAPPABGAFGEFDECC&QUEST=449&j=^R1

special_tiles.title: Hotton Blacksmith
special_tiles.description: Ward may be an oldie but he's a goodie. As soon as you enter his shop you are greeted with a big smile. He shows you to a chair and gives you his catalog to browse.

special_tiles.title: Hotton General Store
special_tiles.description: Ooh the aroma is delicious! Mrs. Barryjam is wearing a brown dress, candy apple red apron, and is winking at you. She also happens to be sampling her famous jam.

special_tiles.title: Hotton Park
special_tiles.description: What a fun place to meet with your friends and play on this gorgeous summer day!

special_tiles.title: Hotton Groomer
special_tiles.description: Looking around you notice the place is glowing. Mr. Klippit is a nut about cleanliness. He has just finished wiping off the door knob you touched when entering. It's rumored that he wanted to be a surgeon but that didn't work out for him. He walks back to his client and says to his assistant Trudy "Scalpel please." And she proceeds to hand him the razor.

special_tiles.title: Hotton Grocery
special_tiles.description: You can't help but sing the Clementine song in your head and you try to contain yourself as you walk in. You fling open the door and notice the store has a wonderful citrus smell. You also notice that there is some freshly made lemonade being offered for free.

special_tiles.title: Bubba's Rock Shop
special_tiles.description: You see a lot of rocks and a large man named Bubba. You know this because he has his name on his shirt. He has sweat stains around his armpits and is muttering something about agates. As you approach the counter he glances at you and sighs. Under his far from fresh smelling breath he mutters "Hope this one buys something or I'll have to close up the shop."

special_tiles.title: Dolly's Inn
special_tiles.description: The door reads in big letters Dolly says "Come on in and take a load off." Wow, that's quite the statement. You wander in and are welcomed by the sweet smell of perfume and Dolly at your side.

special_tiles.title: Rose's Flower Garden
special_tiles.description: There is no one home but there are flowers everywhere. Some are in arrangements and some  are waiting in piles. Rose must be at her shop next door.

special_tiles.title: Rose Thorne's Flower Shop
special_tiles.description: The shop smells of roses.  Everywhere you look there are white roses.

special_tiles.title: Rose's Flower Garden
special_tiles.description: Beautiful flowers are growing all around you.  This must be where Rose grows all of her flowers for her shop.

special_tiles.title: Hotton Gazebo
special_tiles.description: This is the Hotton Gazebo. You can think clearly here and rest your horse for a bit if you'd like. It sure is peaceful.

special_tiles.title: Hotton Vet
special_tiles.description: Busy place here... the phone is ringing continuously and the lobby is full.

special_tiles.title: Ricardo's Cabin
special_tiles.description:
Ricardo likes it hot! His cabin is steamy, he likes to take long hot baths, eat spicy food, sweat in hot weather and drink hot liquids. He also likes to take his vacations anywhere that has a volcano or salsa dancing.
^T6Paint Ricardo's Picture^BMpainting.swf?PAINTING=10&QUEST=143&j=^R1

special_tiles.title: Intersection of Caliente Street and Piquant Lane
Intersection of Caliente Street and Sizzle Street
Intersection of Caliente Street and Solar Flare Boulevard
Intersection of Caliente Street and Sun Lane
Intersection of Caliente Street and Fever Avenue
Intersection of Caliente Street and Swelter Street
Intersection of Caliente Street and Tropic Lane
Intersection of Caliente Street and Arid Avenue
Intersection of Caliente Street and Steamy Street
Intersection of Caliente Street and Balmy Road
Intersection of Caliente Street and Scorching Street
Intersection of Caliente Street and Spicy Street
Hotton Gear Store
special_tiles.description: Hello? Is anyone here? It's so quiet and there are no customers. Hmm... you hear what sounds like a snore. You follow the sound and you catch Sadie laying on the floor in the storeroom taking a nap.

special_tiles.title: Mare Isle Docks
special_tiles.description: A small and simple dock that isn't used much, except by the the only resident, Trina.

special_tiles.title: Cattle Herding
special_tiles.description:
Herd the Cattle!
^T4View the best times for this game^BSTCattle Herding^R1

special_tiles.title: Alexi's Cabin
special_tiles.description:
Upon entering this cabin you see that Alexi must be a busy person. There are papers scattered everywhere. You see another room off to the right and hear noises coming from there.
^T5Help Alexi with some accounting work.^BMaccounting^R1^X^Z

special_tiles.title: Hotton Construction Job
special_tiles.description:
There is a construction site here. If you wanted to help them assemble wooden panels, they will pay you!^T6Easy Job^BMpuzzle1.swf?LEVEL=EASY&j=^R1^T6Medium Job^BMpuzzle1.swf?LEVEL=MEDIUM&j=^R1^T6Hard Job^BMpuzzle1.swf?LEVEL=HARD&j=^R1
^T4View the top scores for this game^BSHConstruction Job^R1^X^Z

special_tiles.title: Bee's Nest
special_tiles.description: There are lots of bees here!  If you want though, you could try to take their honeycomb...^T4Steal Honeycomb from Bees^BMbees^R1

special_tiles.title: Bee's Nest
special_tiles.description: There are lots of bees here!  If you want though, you could try to take their honeycomb...^T4Steal Honeycomb from Bees^BMbees^R1

special_tiles.title: Evelynn's Cabin
special_tiles.description: There is a strong smell of honey throughout the small cabin.  Evelynn is in the kitchen with an apron on.

special_tiles.title: Bee's Nest
special_tiles.description: There are lots of bees here!  If you want though, you could try to take their honeycomb...^T4Steal Honeycomb from Bees^BMbees^R1

special_tiles.title: Horse Dress-Up
special_tiles.description: There is a toy horse here, and people take turns dressing it up as pretty as it can be.  Can you make it prettier than the last person left it?

special_tiles.title: Accalia's Cabin
special_tiles.description: All around you there are cats.  Not only that, but there are pictures and figurines of cats and kittens on all the shelves throughout the cabin.

special_tiles.title: Quinn's Cabin
special_tiles.description: Pressing the doorbell (yes, he has a doorbell) someone shouts to you, "Come in, Come in, Come in." That must be Quinn. He answers the door and invites you in. His cabin has water everywhere. Tiny pools, water in the sink, the bathub is full, water sculptures of some sort, paintings of water, fountains, you name it and he's got it. An odd fellow but it dawns on you that living on Desert Isle and having a water theme  cabin may not be that odd after all.

special_tiles.title: Lajita's Cabin
special_tiles.description: After meeting Lajita's little boy outside of the cabin you are not sure if you want to go in. The boy is very sweet and likes to talk a lot but it is tiring and he must have gotten it from someone (uh hmmm, clearing your throat, his mother) and you really don't have much time for chit chat today. However, the smell of good food is sucking you in.

special_tiles.title: Cadence's Cabin
special_tiles.description: Cadence sprints to the door to greet you. She is all smiles dressed in a red shirt with overalls and her hair tied back with a red and white checkered handkerchief. She offers you something to drink and tells you about her garden.

special_tiles.title: Ormand's Cabin
special_tiles.description: Ormand lives alone and doesn't have much food in his cabin. You see one apple, one banana, a couple pieces of bread and some peanut butter. He tells you that he made his peanut butter by hand. A very worn book lays over his chair. He must have read it a hundred times.

special_tiles.title: Treeton Barn
special_tiles.description: It's so quiet.  The only noise you hear is a light rustling and beautiful music softly playing.  Each of the stalls is large and roomy with clean food and water in the corners.

special_tiles.title: Appleton Barn
special_tiles.description: There are a few horses resting in here. You wander over and chat with their owners a bit.

special_tiles.title: Abandoned Shack
special_tiles.description: A rickety door barely hangs on it's leather hinges.  Could someone possibly live here?  Entering the cabin carefully so that the door doesn't fall off you see a small fire burning in the fireplace and a very old hunched over man sitting in a creaking rocking chair staring into the fire.

special_tiles.title: Beach Shack
special_tiles.description: This shack is exactly that... a shack. It's falling down and you are thinking twice about entering. Peering through the window, you see some food and a blanket in the corner. Is someone actually living here?

special_tiles.title: Lief's Cottage
special_tiles.description: You knock on Lief's door and it creaks open but you cannot see anyone yet. All of a sudden a little girl pops out to greet you. This must be Lief's daughter you think. She smiles at you and says that her dad will be with you in a jiffy. The cottage is overflowing with flowers. His daughter is excitedly dancing around them and at that point you realize she is the one filling the home with daisies. How cute.

special_tiles.title: Cosmo's Cottage
special_tiles.description: What is your sign? This is etched in the cottage door with a star above it. As you enter Cosmo is eager to serve you tea and cookies. The cottage is dark but yet there are many little lights decorating it. There are heavy blue velvet curtains instead of doors. The ceiling has stars and moons on it that are glowing. Rumor has it that Cosmo is known for his fortune telling. He has had great success. He looks down at your hands and smirks at you.

special_tiles.title: Breezy's Cottage
special_tiles.description: You knock on the door but no one answers. Peeking in the window you can see that Breezy's cottage is simple. Not much for furniture. A plain bowl sits on the table filled with fruits and vegetables.

special_tiles.title: Autumn's Cottage
special_tiles.description: On the way to Autumn's cottage a beautiful flower garden catches your eye. Walking around to the front door you see there are 2 vegetable gardens in this lovely place. Knock Knock. Autumn answers the door in her pajamas and her son runs around her legs. She has a pot of oatmeal cooking on the stove and a big vase fillled with flowers on the table. There are toys and books all over the cottage. Autumn is the caretaker of Sunshine Meadows and she tries hard to keep her residents happy.

special_tiles.title: Sunshine Meadows Wishing Well
special_tiles.description: Here you are at the wishing well. Let your horse throw in a couple coins if you have some.

special_tiles.title: Autumn's Garden
special_tiles.description: Walking around Autumn's garden you see that she is using leaves mixed with shredded books as mulch. You wonder if these vegetables taste as good as your standard veggie.

special_tiles.title: Pond
special_tiles.description: It took you a bit to get here with all those thick bushes but you made it. Why not stay a while and relax?

special_tiles.title: Pond
special_tiles.description: Surrounded by bushes like a castle with a moat but you prevailed with a only a few minor scratches from crawling through the bushes. Your horse does not look as happy as you do though.

special_tiles.title: Abandoned Old Beach Shack
special_tiles.description: Upon pushing the door open you notice this little shack has become home to some of the sea's various creatures.  Several crabs are crabbling around,  and a few snails are clinging in the corner... There is also a strange spider on the far wall... After looking closer, you rub your eyes... the letters H-E-L-P have rather unmistakenly been constructed into the latest Web!

special_tiles.title: Soaring Meadows Pond
special_tiles.description: There is always a nice cool breeze in Soaring Meadows and as you walk up to the pond you are greeted by a gentle mist rising off the pond.

special_tiles.title: Soaring Meadows Pond
special_tiles.description: There is always a nice cool breeze in Soaring Meadows and as you walk up to the pond you are being misted with water.

special_tiles.title: Willow's Cottage
special_tiles.description: Willow is the new kid in town. He kindly invites you in and tells you that he's very shy and finds it hard to deal with Harmony and Melody adoring him all the time. You wonder why he doesn't marry one of these gals so he will not be so lonely. His cottage is so bare and quiet.

special_tiles.title: Rainey's Cottage
special_tiles.description: Rainey has just recently moved in to this small community.  Her brother, Cosmo, lives in Sunshine Meadows far away.  You see a picture of him on the wall.

special_tiles.title: Harmony's Cottage
special_tiles.description: There is a large welcome sign on the door with musical notes surrounding it. No surprise here with a name like Harmony. Although you've heard that she is a little touchy about her music, being that she doesn't get as much credit as her sister Melody does. Her cottage is decked out with the latest and greatest in musical instruments. She even has a lamp in the shape of a violin.

special_tiles.title: Melody's Cottage
special_tiles.description: Melody has a lot of energy as you see her jumping up and down in the window and waving at you. Like her sister, Melody also has a sign on her door, but hers reads "You aren't having fun unless you're with Melody."  Melody throws open the door and pulls you in. She starts singing loudly and laughing. Her cottage has bright linens and lots of flowers. She has pieces of music framed and hanging on her walls.

special_tiles.title: River's Cottage
special_tiles.description: River lives here with her grandfather Frederick. He recently moved in after he started having trouble taking care of all the chores around his cabin.  River now looks after the kind old man. He in turn cooks wonderful meals for her using recipes long forgotten by the latest generations.

special_tiles.title: Storm and Sunny's Cottage
special_tiles.description: The recently married couple, Storm and Sunny, live here. It's been said no two people love each other more, yet these two always seem to be fighting over something. Nothing serious, but always bickering back and forth.  Oddly though,  they are always smiling while "fighting".  You wonder if it's not just the way they like to communicate.  It makes for a noisy house though!  One should be sure to never get in the middle of one of their arguments!

special_tiles.title: Griffin's Cabin
special_tiles.description: Griffin seems to live in comfort. Some nice cushy chairs and couches make up one room. Griffin seems content to sit in his chair waiting for visitors.

special_tiles.title: Judith's Cabin
special_tiles.description: Tobias lives with his mother Judith. Upon entering you are overwhelmed by a chocolate smell. Judith is at the stove melting chocolate and mixing it with crushed hazelnuts. Smells yummy. Tobias mentions that he loves chocolate spread and has it for breakfast lunch and dinner! He also dips everything in it. He offers you a taste.

special_tiles.title: Ira's Cabin
special_tiles.description: There is no sign of the birthday decorations that had previously filled the place. Instead, you can finally see that Ira's home is filled with posters of mountainous scenes. There are some cross-country skis hanging on the wall and you see a heavy snow coat hanging near the door.

special_tiles.title: Nadine's Cabin
special_tiles.description:
Nadine is an artist. Her home is scattered with paints, brushes and canvas. She has paintings hanging on every wall in her cabin and even some on the ceiling. (She tells you that she enjoys looking at them while in bed and drifting off to sleep) You wonder if this could help your own insomnia, perhaps she would let you buy one. There is one odd thing here though, Nadine only paints flowers.
^T6Paint Nadine's Flower^BMpainting.swf?PAINTING=2&QUEST=144&j=^R1

special_tiles.title: The Bird's Nest Cabin
special_tiles.description: Mack and Janeen named their cabin to reflect their love of watching birds. Known as Boppie and Nana to their granddaughter Violet, they share their love of birding and nature with her. The cabin is very cozy inside and typically smells like cinnamon and apples. Janeen can usually be found in the kitchen making some kind of apple dessert.

special_tiles.title: Ocean Turbulence
special_tiles.description: Look at those waves pounding the shoreline!

special_tiles.title: Hazel's Cabin
special_tiles.description: You knock on the door and Hazel shouts "Come in if you can."  You try to open the door but it won't budge. Through the crack of the door you see piles and piles of nuts strewn about. What in the world? Hazel sees you struggling and comes to help.

special_tiles.title: Jasper and Jillian's Cabin
special_tiles.description: There are several giant chalkboards covered with poetry. Must be Jasper's work! Jillian is busy straightening up the place. You notice strewn about notepads and pencils. Jasper must be really focused on his poetry!^T6Play the piano for Jasper^BMpianist.swf?TUNE=CDEFGABP&QUEST=188&j=^R1

special_tiles.title: Ocean Turbulence
special_tiles.description: Look at those waves pounding the shoreline!

special_tiles.title: Ocean Turbulence
special_tiles.description: This part of the island sure takes a beating from the ocean waves.

special_tiles.title: Stella's Cabin
special_tiles.description: Stella is a big fish eater. She knows her fish well and knows the best way to prepare them. While you are walking around her cabin you get the drift that she wants you to ask her some fish questions. She frequents all the fish markets around Horse Isle and if interested might be able to help you find a good deal. She offers you a piece of smoked salmon.

special_tiles.title: Trail Riding
special_tiles.description:
You can try to follow a challenging trail here with your horse! ^T6Trail Riding!^BMtrailriding^R1
^T4View the top scores for this game^BSHTrail Riding^R1
^X^Z

special_tiles.title: Orbital Game Room
special_tiles.description:
2 Player turn-based game, where the object is to capture more orbs than your opponent.  
^T4View the top scores for this game^BSWOrbital^R1

special_tiles.title: Wington Pets
special_tiles.description: You are amazed at how clean and quiet it is in here. All the animals look so sweet. It will be hard to decide. If only your horse could talk. Well, you've heard Kay is good at suggesting a particular pet for each horse.

special_tiles.title: Whiskerton Pets
special_tiles.description: Rusty is a funny guy. He loves his pet shop. You can tell he finds it hard to sell them. You've seen him cry while selling two pets just since you've been here. Then he's all smiles and cracking cat jokes.

special_tiles.title: Treeton Pets
special_tiles.description: There is an interesting variety of pets in this store.  All the animals look like they have clean homes and seem to enjoy themselves, even though they don't have a real home yet.

special_tiles.title: Appleton Pets
special_tiles.description: Mr. Leash is well stocked. He's coming towards you and seems very friendly. Like other pet stores you have been to this one isn't too different. It has the same smell of pine shavings and wet dog. Your horse is looking a little lonely these days though and it might be nice to give it a friend.

special_tiles.title: Shellton Pet Shoppe
special_tiles.description: This is an adorable pet shoppe and even more adorable is Ollie. You can't help but smile at him.  He is so friendly and never frowns. You have a look around and he keeps checking on you to see if you need help. The pets are very neatly groomed and all have bows around their necks. Except of course for the spider but it comes in a fancy box (with a cute bow on top).

special_tiles.title: Hotton Pets
special_tiles.description: You are amazed at the amount of customers Jaxon has. He's telling some sort of story now about how he saved a kitten from a pond. He's the town hero. He also lets all of his pets run around the store, they are cage free. He doesn't think it's humane to keep them locked up. Needless to say it's a bit of a zoo in here and watch where you step.

special_tiles.title: Kendi's Hut
special_tiles.description: Kendi is a cute little girl who lives with her mom Yazhi and her dad Yiska. She makes sand sculptures and sand soup complete with sticks and stones. She might even offer you some if you talk with her.

special_tiles.title: Sando's Hut
special_tiles.description: At first glance Sando's hut doesn't seem to have much but then you notice 5 barrels stacked along the right side. Sando starts to play music with his recorder and snakes begin rising slowly out of the barrels. You are deciding whether to go in for a closer look or make like a tree and leave.

special_tiles.title: Mandala's Hut
special_tiles.description:
You walk up to Mandala's hut and a rock near the door is painted to read "If you will work for food, then please come in." Well, that is the strangest sign you have ever seen but you are a little hungry so you knock.
^T6Help Mandala with her cookie cutter^BMcookiecutter.swf?COOKIE=4&QUEST=1311&j=^R1

special_tiles.title: Loyada's Hut
special_tiles.description: Loyada is an older woman who loves small talk. Her hut smells like peppermint candy and tea. She asks you to have a seat. She continues rocking in her chair and begins telling you all about the sand storm years ago that swallowed up her precious emerald necklace given to her by her late husband.

special_tiles.title: Alati's Hut
special_tiles.description: Knock Knock. You hear a faint cry for help. You open the door and see no one. Hmm... "HELP, in the back outside." You run to the back door and see Alati sinking in the sand. What on earth? He explains that he is a man of many ideas and he built shoes that could walk across quicksand. Unfortunately, many of his ideas flop. He asks for your help.

special_tiles.title: Chillton General Store
special_tiles.description: The store is quite small, but it still carries the necessities as well as some hot cocoa.  It is also quite warm in here.  Especially after being in the cold outside.

special_tiles.title: Prison Work Area
special_tiles.description: To leave you must complete the community service of making gravel.^T6Work for Release^BMjail.swf?QUEST=311&ROCKS=8&j=^R1

special_tiles.title: Crumbling Cabin
special_tiles.description: The door is barely hanging on the hinges, In fact, spider webs may be the only things holding it up. Are you sure you really want to step inside? Your horse neighs a warning from behind you.

special_tiles.title: Earton Pet Shop
special_tiles.description: Lots of commotion! There is so much noise you can barely think. Dogs barking, birds squawking, kitties meowing, etc. There are also tons of feathers flying through the air. There must have been a bird fight.

special_tiles.title: Cozy Home
special_tiles.description: Seeking shelter from the bitter cold you knock on door and step inside.  As you glance around you notice a young woman sitting at a table peeling apples.  The smell of fresh baked apple pie permeates the air.  She looks up from her task startled but smiles at you.

special_tiles.title: Bee's Nest
special_tiles.description: There are lots of bees here! If you want though, you could try to take their honeycomb...^T4Steal Honeycomb from Bees^BMbees.swf?m=^R1

special_tiles.title: Butterfly Catch
special_tiles.description: Butterflies flying high, catch them if you can! ^T5 Butterfly Catch ^BMbutterflycatch^R1^T4View the top scores for this game^BSHButterfly Catch^R1^X^Z

special_tiles.title: Shellton Barn
special_tiles.description: This barn is out of the way of the main traffic of Shellton.  All the stalls are clean and well kept.

special_tiles.title: Horse Word Guess
special_tiles.description: If you can guess what the Horse Phrase is,  you win!^T6Horse Word Guess^BMwordguess^R1^T4View the top scores for this game^BSHHorse Word Guess^R1^X^Z

special_tiles.title: Daf's Cottage
special_tiles.description: There are flowers all over this small cabin.  You look out in the garden and see Daf picking flowers into a large woven basket.

special_tiles.title: Wington Food Store
special_tiles.description: This little store smells of fresh fruit.  It is a small, cramped place, but Cara obviously enjoys her job as the place is immaculately clean.

special_tiles.title: Cactus Dress-Up
special_tiles.description: There's a cactus here to dress up. Please be careful not to poke yourself!

special_tiles.title: Balloon Game
special_tiles.description:
Collect the blue bubbles and avoid the red ones! ^T6Hot Air Balloon^BMhotairballoon^R1
^T4View the top scores for this game^BSHHot Air Balloon^R1
^X^Z

special_tiles.title: Daedalus' Cabin
special_tiles.description: You enter and find feathers everywhere!  To the back of the cabin you see an old man bent over a wooden frame that resembles a pair of wings.  A young boy, Daedalus' son Icarus is busily stirring a pot of melted wax.

special_tiles.title: Chillton Poetry Room
special_tiles.description: Within this room hovers a peaceful poetic atmosphere. It is suggested that minds can come together in here and arrange words into simple harmony.  Any thoughts remaining when you leave will remain intact for the next lucky visitor.

special_tiles.title: Santon Poetry Room
special_tiles.description: Within this room hovers a peaceful poetic atmosphere. It is suggested that minds can come together in here and arrange words into simple harmony.  Any thoughts remaining when you leave will remain intact for the next lucky visitor.

special_tiles.title: Ant Hill #3
special_tiles.description:
If you wish, you could help the Ant within this Ant Hill store his food!
^T6Help in Ant Hill #3^BManthillz.swf?HILL=3&QUEST=233&j=^R1
^T4View the top scores for this game^BSHAntHill #3^R1^X^Z

special_tiles.title: Trina's Cabin
special_tiles.description: The cabin is small, but well put together.  Everything has its place including horse tack neatly put away in the corner.  There is a refreshing leather scent throughout the building.

special_tiles.title: Start of a path
special_tiles.description: This appears to be a lightly used path through this forest... Very hard to tell which way it continues from here...

special_tiles.title: Inkton Docks
special_tiles.description: Watching the boats go by you see a stand that has the list of places to go.  So many places to go so little time.

special_tiles.title: Inkton Art Room #6
special_tiles.description:
In this cabin there is a giant easel with lots of pens. Everyone who enters is encouraged to go ahead and doodle alone or together.

DUE TO ABUSE - Only subscribers' drawings may be seen by other players.

special_tiles.title: Inkton Art Room #5
special_tiles.description:
In this cabin there is a giant easel with lots of pens. Everyone who enters is encouraged to go ahead and doodle alone or together.

DUE TO ABUSE - Only subscribers' drawings may be seen by other players.

special_tiles.title: Inkton Art Room #4
special_tiles.description:
In this cabin there is a giant easel with lots of pens. Everyone who enters is encouraged to go ahead and doodle alone or together.

DUE TO ABUSE - Only subscribers' drawings may be seen by other players.

special_tiles.title: Inkton Art Room #3
special_tiles.description:
In this cabin there is a giant easel with lots of pens. Everyone who enters is encouraged to go ahead and doodle alone or together.

DUE TO ABUSE - Only subscribers' drawings may be seen by other players.

special_tiles.title: Inkton Art Room #2
special_tiles.description:
In this cabin there is a giant easel with lots of pens. Everyone who enters is encouraged to go ahead and doodle alone or together.

DUE TO ABUSE - Only subscribers' drawings may be seen by other players.

special_tiles.title: Welcome to Inkton!
special_tiles.description:
This is a small community that loves art.  Come draw in one of the many drawing rooms!
^X^Z

special_tiles.title: Painted Pony Inn
special_tiles.description: Whew... it's a bit hot in here but there is music playing which has piqued your interest. Remy veers your way and greets you. He points to a bench and suggests that you take a load off and eat some good grub.

special_tiles.title: Gem Slider
special_tiles.description:
The gems in cases here have been messed up!  They need to be put back into the original pattern... but... you can't open the cases!
^T6Easy^BMgemslider.swf?LEVEL=EASY&j=^R1
^T6Medium^BMgemslider.swf?LEVEL=MEDIUM&j=^R1
^T6Hard^BMgemslider.swf?LEVEL=HARD&j=^R1
^T4View the top scores for this game^BSHGem Slider^R1^X^Z

special_tiles.title: Storage Hut
special_tiles.description: This odd little cabin is full of seed packets!  Who would ever try to grow something in the desert?

special_tiles.title: Sandcastle Moat #15
special_tiles.description:
^T6Straighten out the Moat^BMsandcastlemoat.swf?BOARD=15&QUEST=455&j=^R1

^X^Z

special_tiles.title: Genevieve's Cottage
special_tiles.description: You knock and hear a sweet voice say "Please come in, I'm busy at the potter's wheel."  The door creaks as you open it.  A very earthy smell and a hot blast of air rushes toward you from the kiln.  Everything except the furniture is clay.  She has a whole room full of colorful, finished pieces.

special_tiles.title: Salvador's Cottage
special_tiles.description: The outside of Salvador's cottage is decorated with illustrations. You enter and see that the inside is also covered with drawings. Hanging from each wall is a marker with a message that reads "Art is my life, this is my life in ink, please add to it. Draw something meaningful... Salvador." Unable to resist the request, you reach for the marker.

special_tiles.title: Mona's Cottage
special_tiles.description:
Her cottage smells like green tea and sandalwood. She has many sculptures in her home. Mona motions you to come to the kitchen and points out the window. You look and see that she has an incredible sculpture garden.
^T6Help Mona with her cookie cutter^BMcookiecutter.swf?COOKIE=7&QUEST=1315&j=^R1

special_tiles.title: Pablo's Cottage
special_tiles.description: There is paint splattered all about in here. Very bright, fun colors. Pablo is hanging another canvas on the wall. He turns to you and smiles. "Another one done and the rest of my life to go, there is nothing I enjoy more." You glance at his table and notice some beautiful pieces of pottery you have seen somewhere before. He invites you to sit down and asks if you'd like a canvas.

special_tiles.title: Mona's Sculpture Garden
special_tiles.description: Beautiful and intriguing sculptures of all kinds lie in this garden. While you are walking through you rest a minute on the stone bench, take in the fresh air and ponder her art.

special_tiles.title: Old Man Gritty's Shack
special_tiles.description: You push open the shack door, feeling confident that no one is around, when all of a sudden Gritty jumps out at you. "What are YOU doing here? You better have a good reason why you are breaking into my shack and oogling my collections."

special_tiles.title: Holly's Cottage
special_tiles.description: You trudge through the deep snow making your way to the door. Whew! You weren't sure if you were going to make it. Knock. Knock. Holly comes to the door and invites you in. It smells wonderful inside. Scents of peppermint and molasses fill the air. Holly enjoys collecting and she has everything in beautiful glass cabinets. Each one neatly labeled with when and where she found each treasure. She invites you to sit down.

A woman wearing a linen dress of orange and green is creating a new masterpiece at the small table in the center of the room.

special_tiles.title: Welcome to Whiskerton!
special_tiles.description: Welcome to Cat Isle and the town of Whiskerton. We welcome all travelers except ... well we aren't very fond of dogs.^X^Z

special_tiles.title: Whiskerton General
special_tiles.description: "Hello my friend. Please, take a look around and let me know what I can sell you."  This is a store with a wide variety of the usual items but the ambiance is different... Lanterns strung from the ceiling, cuckoo clock meowing slightly off time, and the smell of catnip.

special_tiles.title: Whiskerton Vet
special_tiles.description: The receptionist is very friendly and helpful. She directs you to Dr. Feelbedder who is a respectable man in these parts. You are assured that your animals will be given top care.

special_tiles.title: Whiskerton Feed
special_tiles.description: Well, hello there! Can I help you? I am here if you need anything please don't be shy!"  That is certainly a nice greeting, kind of puts you right into the buying mood.

special_tiles.title: Whiskerton Groomer
special_tiles.description: There is horse hair everywhere.  Things seem a bit askew.  Buckets and brushes are thrown everywhere.  Hopefully Shaylene does a better job on your horse than she does on keeping up her place.

special_tiles.title: Krista's House and Catnip Gardens
special_tiles.description:
The inside of the house is in better shape than the gardens outside, although the scent of catnip is very strong. Large baskets of flowers are all over the room. There is no way all those flowers are grown in that garden.
^T6Help Krista with her cookie cutter^BMcookiecutter.swf?COOKIE=9&QUEST=1317&j=^R1

special_tiles.title: Catnip Gardens
special_tiles.description: There is not much for flowers here.  It seems to be mostly catnip that has been chewed on by the local cat pack.

special_tiles.title: Carrotton Barn
special_tiles.description: Odd. This barn doesn't smell like horses, it must be new. You wander around and see Dwight hanging lanterns.

special_tiles.title: Carrotton Rock Shop
special_tiles.description: Evidently, the rock shop supports Grey Slate's hobby; all around you see the work of an expert gold- and silver-smith.  Slate has made everything from rings and chains to beautiful figurines and fancy bits and buckles.  His shop glitters with his work.

special_tiles.title: Carrotton General
special_tiles.description: Squeaky floorboards are the first thing you notice in here. It's hard to hear Betsy talk with the constant creaking. Although as more people enter the store she begins to shout so she is obviously aware of this. Ms. Burlap explains to you how much she loves her job as you look past her with boredom trying to remember what you needed.

special_tiles.title: Carrotton Drawing Room
special_tiles.description:
In this cabin there is a giant easel with lots of pens. Everyone who enters is encouraged to go ahead and doodle alone or together.

DUE TO ABUSE - Only subscribers' drawings may be seen by other players.

special_tiles.title: Carrotton Docks
special_tiles.description: Laughing as water splashes, you carefully pick your way around the slippery deck.

special_tiles.title: Welcome to Carrotton!
special_tiles.description: Greetings and welcome to our spunky little town. Our population can easily be counted on two hands but we make it up for it with hospitality.

special_tiles.title: Shell Shifter
special_tiles.description: ^T5Find the two balls under the shells.^BMshellshifter^R1^T4View the top scores for this game^BSHShell Shifter^R1^X^Z

special_tiles.title: Easter Bunny's Cabin
special_tiles.description: This cabin is quite different from ones you have seen.  There are eggs everywhere, as well as baskets, dried grass, and berries for dyeing the eggs.  There doesn't seem to be a lot of furniture around either.  Just a table and chair and a comfy looking cushion.

special_tiles.title: Fly N' Frog
special_tiles.description: Eat as many flies as possible... and don't fall in the water!^T5Fly N' Frog^BMflynfrog^R1^T4View the top scores for this game^BSHFly N Frog^R1^X^Z

special_tiles.title: Nina's Shack
special_tiles.description: Walking down the path you come to a small shack. It seems as though no one is around.  In the distance a hawk cries out.  After knocking on the door a tall middle age woman answers.  On her arm is a small falcon.  She smiles and beckons you to come inside where there are birds of every shape and size flying about.

special_tiles.title: Murray's Cabin
special_tiles.description: Murray is the groundskeeper for Tail Isle.  He must be busy maintaining the unsold ranches.  The door is locked and the windows are shut up tight.

special_tiles.title: Tail Isle Boat Dock
special_tiles.description: Wow. This is one small dock. Hopefully the dinky boat tied up here will get you to your destination without a swim involved. On the bright side, the waters are calm and clear. Looks like a great place to fish.

special_tiles.title: Tail Isle Wagon Station
special_tiles.description: Not very well kept up, this wagon station will at least cut down travel time between here and the end of Tail Isle, which can be a long jog.

special_tiles.title: Tail End Wagon Station
special_tiles.description: A small, but well kept, station that is just the way to travel to get near the boat dock.

special_tiles.title: Tail End General Store
special_tiles.description: This store is very remote but is also quite convienent for the local ranch owners.

special_tiles.title: Rebecca's Homestead
special_tiles.description: Upon entering the small cabin, you are overwhelmed with the smell of sawdust.  There is wood everywhere.  Some smoothed, some rough, some beautifully shaped.  Rebecca must love carpentry.

special_tiles.title: Evan & Joanna's Cabin
special_tiles.description:
This is obviously a very musically talented family. The cabin is filled with the harmonies of different instruments.
^T6Help Joanna with her cookie cutter^BMcookiecutter.swf?COOKIE=5&QUEST=1313&j=^R1

special_tiles.title: Did you just see something sparkly in the air?
There's some interesting sparkly dust motes in this area.
Tucker's Cabin
special_tiles.description: You approach the cabin and Tucker is outside on his porch swing playing his banjo. He greets you and asks you if you want to have a seat. That's very nice of him so you make your way towards the door when all of a sudden he jumps in front of you, throws himself against the front door.

special_tiles.title: Karl's Cabin
special_tiles.description: Looking around the relatively large cabin, you wonder how anyone could live like this.  There are pails of something thick all over.  Some seems to have slopped on the floor.  From the looks of it, it is quite sticky.

special_tiles.title: Geo Hunt
special_tiles.description: ^T5Find the correct country.^BMgeohunt^R1^T4View the top scores for this game^BSHGeo Hunt^R1^X^Z

special_tiles.title: Jewelry Workshop
special_tiles.description: Inside the workshop there's a desk where Jade is able to work on all the jewelry that comes into her workshop.  There are boxes of tools as well as gold and silver ore remnants everywhere.

special_tiles.title: Vegetable Garden
special_tiles.description: You are welcome to tend this garden. It only produces carrots when kept weed free.^T6Weed the Garden!^BMweeding^R1^X^Z

special_tiles.title: Whiskerton Docks
special_tiles.description: The sun shining brightly reflects off the sails of the boats.  The rainbows of the sea.

special_tiles.title: Balloon Pop
special_tiles.description:
Pop the balloons in the correct order!
^T5Balloon Pop^BMballoonpop^R1^T4View the top scores for this game^BSHBalloon Pop^R1^X^Z

special_tiles.description: A nice little rock shop that has quite the displays.  The prices are so good and they're so far away from everything that you wonder how they make much of a living.

special_tiles.title: Bailey's Homestead
special_tiles.description: Upon entering the cabin you see a note on the table: Welcome Visitor, I am out for a walk. Feel free to wander around. If you want to leave the island you will need to come find me. -Bailey

special_tiles.description: This dock looks out onto azure waters that sparkle in the hot sunlight.

special_tiles.title: Sand Isles Docks

special_tiles.title: Feed Workshop
special_tiles.description: This place smells of hay and molasses.  There are huge bins all over filled with different types of horse food and counters and shelves filled with utensils.

special_tiles.title: Sandy General
special_tiles.description: Being the only store for quite a ways probably helps this little place, but only the necessities are here.  You can sell most anything you like however.

special_tiles.title: Jubal's Teepee
special_tiles.description: Jubal is on a small stool in the middle of the teepee.  He appears to be braiding a rope that winds around inside the entire teepee.

special_tiles.title: Palila's Teepee
special_tiles.description: Palila's teepee is full of jewelry boxes.  Palila is sitting off to the right carving an intricate lid for her next box.

special_tiles.title: Miner's Shack
special_tiles.description: The miner's hut is dark and dusty.  There are lots of shovels and rock picks.  Small bins in the back are labled "GOLD", "IRON", "COPPER" and "SILVER".

special_tiles.title: Word Lock Colors

special_tiles.title: Cantle Meadows Gazebo
special_tiles.description: This is the meeting place for the residents of Cantle Meadows.

special_tiles.title: Oasis
special_tiles.description: Ah! A refreshing oasis. A perfect place to cool off after a hot trek through the scorching desert.

special_tiles.title: Hold Your Horses
special_tiles.description: Try to keep all your horses within the circle!^T5Hold your horses.^BMholdyourhorses^R1^T4View the top scores for this game^BSHHold Your Horses^R1^X^Z

special_tiles.title: Brea's Shanty
special_tiles.description:
This small, brokendown shack is sparingly decorated. The sunlight shining in the windows shows sand all over, but mostly on the floor. There is a note on a table in the middle of the room:
Welcome visitor,
I'm out for a walk on my little island. Feel free to find me if you like, or be on your merry way.
Brea

special_tiles.title: Witherton Bank
special_tiles.description:
This venerable building is designed in a graceful and stately way. It inspires confidence.
Note: A max of $9,999,999,999 is allowed to be held in the bank and a max of $2,147,483,647 on hand.

special_tiles.title: Posy's Home
special_tiles.description: Upon entering you are overwhelmed by a flowery smell.  There are dried flowers hanging everywhere and live ones in vases spread around the rooms.

special_tiles.title: Posy's Garden
special_tiles.description: Though small, this garden contains many flowers, colors and smells.

special_tiles.title: Blacksmith Workshop
special_tiles.description: There is an anvil in the corner and metal working tools everywhere.  Pieces of ore are laying all over the ground.  Some looks pretty rough still while other pieces look like leftovers from a previous project.

special_tiles.title: Sewing Workshop
special_tiles.description: There is cotton everywhere and bins of dye everywhere.  Not only that, but there are bins filled with all sorts of colors of thread and cloth pieces.

special_tiles.title: Rowboat
special_tiles.description: Move up to go to the ship or you'll be heading back to shore.

special_tiles.title: Pirate Ship
special_tiles.description: This large ship has many emblems of skulls on it.  None with crossbones,  just the skulls.

special_tiles.title: Floria's Cottage
special_tiles.description: The main room as you enter is neatly decorated with small pillows on the chairs and jewelry hanging on the walls from small, delicate hooks.  On a table is a pile of gems, metals and tools for jewelry making as well as bags of cloth, fabric and feathers sitting nearby for other crafts.

special_tiles.title: Conformation Trainer
special_tiles.description: The smell and sound of horses surrounds you.  What a perfect place to do some horse training.

special_tiles.title: Demetrius' House
special_tiles.description: You enter the house and look around you curiously. It seems as though nobody is here; the entire room lies silent and undisturbed. Sunlight streams in through a large window on one side, lighting up the dust motes floating in the air. There are piles of manuscripts and books lying all around the room, on the floor, on wooden tables, or on chairs. You step a little further in to the room when suddenly the faded stuffed chair on the other end swings around to reveal a thin young man with rumpled clothing and a pointed brown goatee. He smiles at you in a friendly, if absent way.

special_tiles.title: Penelope's Cabin
special_tiles.description: There are books scattered and the place looks a bit in shambles.  In a separate, small room a young girl is lying in bed, awake.  Paige seems to not quite know what to do with the mess and her rushing around doesn't seem to be helping her any.

special_tiles.title: Witherton General
special_tiles.description: Witherton General isn't the cleanest shop you've seen.  Some of the shelves are a little crooked and someone has written "DUST ME" on the small cabinet to your right.

special_tiles.title: English Tack Workshop
special_tiles.description: Once you enter you are overwhelmed with the smell of leather.  There are leather pieces, cloth pieces and cotton all over.  Vats in the corner are filled with the different colored dyes and all sorts of tools are piled on tables and in cabinets.

special_tiles.title: Witherton Gear Shop
special_tiles.description: Witherton stocks not only the basic gear in order to make it affordable to ride your horse, but also some of the top quality sets.  It is all perfectly placed around the small shop.

special_tiles.title: Witherton Docks
special_tiles.description: This small dock is the perfect place to catch a boat ride to a few other isles.

special_tiles.title: Horse Run
special_tiles.description: Join with others searching for the Orbs!   More reward based on number of players!

special_tiles.title: Appleton Water Tower
special_tiles.description: A bird's nest sits perched precariously on the side of the water tower. A little black bird peeks out over the top of the nest and stares at you with a curious look.

special_tiles.title: Allaire's Cabin
special_tiles.description: This cabin is full of feathers of all sorts of colors.  They aren't thrown around haphazardly though.  They're hanging on the walls, from the ceiling and off of furniture.

special_tiles.title: Robin's Secret Hollow
special_tiles.description: With the help of Robin's magic, you crawl into a hole under the roots of the weeping willow, and to your surprise, you find yourself in a tidy little home under the ground. There is a warm fireplace to one side, a red and green rug on the hearth, some pictures on the wall and an ivy covered bookshelf in the corner. A little wooden table covered by a bright red cloth sits in the center of the room. Two small chairs are on either side, and it looks as though Robin has set out a lovely tea. Buttered toast, cakes, and mint tea are all laid out, and you wonder if you will get to take part.

special_tiles.title: Rhianna's Cottage
special_tiles.description: It is quite obvious that Rhianna loves to sew.  She has raw cotton everywhere and a spinning wheel as well as piles of finished cloth and a sewing machine.  There are even vats of natural dyes for dying the fabric. ^T6Help Rhianna with her cookie cutter^BMcookiecutter.swf?COOKIE=3&QUEST=1310&j=^R1

special_tiles.title: The Horse Whisperer
special_tiles.description: Welcome to the Horse Whisperer. For $50,000 he can try to locate a wild horse of a particular breed and point it out on the map to you. If there probably isn't a wild horse of that breed right now, he will tell you that also for a lesser fee of $10,000. Be aware. Any other traveler could pay to see the same breed and might beat you to the horse you chose to find. First to catch a wild horse gets to keep it. There is no guarantee that you can reach the horse even if it is found. It will still cost you the full amount!

special_tiles.title: Dieter's Cottage
special_tiles.description: You enter Dieter's cottage and he immediately welcomes you. Something smells delicious in here. The fire has a nice glow and is warming you. Dieter mutters something about chocolate and hands you a stick. Ahhh...he wants you to make s'mores! You glance in the kitchen and see that there are bags and bags of marshmallows as well as an abundance of chocolate and graham crackers. There isn't room for any other food. Could that be all that he eats?

special_tiles.title: Oswald's Cottage
special_tiles.description: Upon entering you are overwhelmed by a musty smell.  There are old maps and books everywhere.  Most of the books seem to deal in the mystical.

special_tiles.title: Bridge Crossing
special_tiles.description: There is a large gap in the bridge and an equally large troll standing in front of you.

special_tiles.title: Crystalton Docks
special_tiles.description: Ice is broken up along the shore and there is ice coating the dock.  Be careful not to slip!

special_tiles.title: Welcome to Crystalton!
special_tiles.description: A small town known for its Geothermal Spring which heats the town and prevents snow from staying long.

special_tiles.title: Crystalton General
special_tiles.description: The store is a bit small and cramped, but they'll still buy most anything you want to sell.  They also always stock the bare necessities.

special_tiles.title: Crystalton Barn
special_tiles.description: This barns looks as if it was built a long time ago.  Though the paint is peeling the stalls are still nice and warm.

special_tiles.title: Elsa's Shack
special_tiles.description: The floor of this shack isn't very level but is bright red.  There's an old woman in the corner hunched over a picture she's drawing of the barn across the road.  Books are piled on every available shelf and table.  The room smells of an odd perfume or soap so you leave quickly before she realizes you're here.

special_tiles.title: Linnea's Cabin
special_tiles.description: Linnea is braiding a rug in the center of the room before a large fireplace.  In one corner is a pile of many colors and patterns of fabric, all torn into long strips.  In a neat pile by the door are a couple dozen braided rugs of varying sizes.

special_tiles.title: Britt's Cabin
special_tiles.description: Britt's cabin smells of pine and sweet breads.  You look on the sturdy blue kitchen table and see braided breads carefully placed in baskets.  There's a blue and white hooked rug on the floor and a yellow striped cat is sleeping peacefully in the window.

special_tiles.title: Kyleigh's Cabin
special_tiles.description: This cabin is neatly organized with everything in its place.  A piano sits in the corner and looks like it gets plenty of use.  Kyleigh is sitting in a chair in the corner reading a rather large book.^T6Play for Kyleigh^BMpianist.swf?TUNE=EEGEDECGGAGFGDPBAGFEDGEDEC&QUEST=592&j=j=^R1

special_tiles.title: Svea and Signe's Cabin
special_tiles.description:
Svea and Signe are twin sisters who have decorated this cabin in a rather odd manner.  One side is decorated in yellow, and the other is decorated in red.  It's easy to see that Svea must like red because of the red ribbons she has braided into her long blonde hair.  Signe is wearing a yellow dress and is knitting a yellow sweater on the yellow side of the room.
^T6Help Svea with her cookie cutter^BMcookiecutter.swf?COOKIE=8&QUEST=1316&j=^R1

special_tiles.title: Mikko's Cabin
special_tiles.description: Mikko strums a guitar while sitting on a small wooden stool by the fireplace.  On the mantle and a few of the walls are beautiful black ink sketches simply framed.  To your right is a desk covered with multiple technical drawings of the fountain in the middle of town.  There is a large dog laying next to Mikko in front of the fire.

special_tiles.title: Cyrstalton's Geothermal Spring
special_tiles.description: This spring heats the entire town, making it an oasis in the middle of Ice Isle.

special_tiles.title: Soren and Anika's House
special_tiles.description: Here lives a happily married couple in a beautifully furnished house.  Soren is looking through a stack of sheet music next to a small piano.  Anika appears to be playing warm-up scales on her flute.  ^T6Play for Soren^BMpianist.swf?TUNE=EGEDCEGEDCDEFGAGFED&QUEST=595&j=^R1

special_tiles.title: Yorick's Cottage
special_tiles.description: This small cozy cottage is a warm escape from the chilly outdoors.  There's a roaring fire in the corner fireplace and a warm pot of stew on the small kitchen table.

special_tiles.title: Rowboat
special_tiles.description: Move up to go to the ship or you'll be heading back to shore.

special_tiles.title: DO NOT ENTER Sign
special_tiles.description: The sign here makes it abundantly clear that company is not wanted.  Could they be referring to you though? ^X^Z

special_tiles.title: Skullton Antiquities
special_tiles.description: The first thing you notice is a giant anchor hanging above a small counter.  There is a pile of ropes sitting in the corner with a few barrels spread around.  Some appear to be filled with water while others are empty.  Hearing someone clear their throat, you see a  well-built teen with a patch covering her right eye.  Surprisingly, she has bright purple hair decorated with beads of onyx and sapphire.

special_tiles.title: Ghost Ship
special_tiles.description: It suddenly looks a lot darker.  Everything is ragged and there is, what appears to be a ghost, angrily floating towards you.

special_tiles.title: Ghost Ship
special_tiles.description: It suddenly looks a lot darker.  Everything is ragged and there is, what appears to be a ghost, angrily floating towards you.

special_tiles.title: Ghost Ship
special_tiles.description: It suddenly looks a lot darker.  Everything is ragged and there is, what appears to be a ghost, angrily floating towards you.

special_tiles.title: Skullton Tavern
special_tiles.description: Mmmm...delicious aromas fill the room. Your mouth is watering. The tavern owner makes her way to you and invites you to dine and take a load off.

special_tiles.title: Skullton General Store
special_tiles.description: George appears to be in the corner sleeping with the chair rocked back on its two rear legs.  Upon your entering the chair's front legs sharply hit the ground and George gives you a bit of a glare.

special_tiles.title: Skullton Headquarters
special_tiles.description: Upon entering the headquarters the first thing you notice is a long table with chairs  lined up around it.  Captain Jack is sitting at the end talking to a parrot that is perched on his shoulder.  There are barrels all around that are filled with jewels and gold of all kinds.

special_tiles.title: Morgan's Tent
special_tiles.description: There is a musty smell in here. The tent is in good condition though. It seems as though Scurvy Gums knows how to keep a clean house. If he could only do the same with those pearly whites or what's left of them. He has pictures of what appears to be family hanging on the walls and there are a few candles barely burning. All the wax has melted onto the table.

special_tiles.title: Bill's Tent
special_tiles.description: This tent is in shambles.  There are papers scattered everywhere.  Some of which look like maps while others seem to be odd writings.

special_tiles.title: Ben's Tent
special_tiles.description: Ick....er I mean hmm...it smells like fish in here. This explains why his name is Barnacle Ben. He's got Barnacles stuck to the walls of his tent and it doesn't make for good woman catching. He also has many torn and tattered jolly roger's hanging about.

special_tiles.title: Annie's Tent
special_tiles.description: Before you even open the tent flap you can hear Annie shouting. You enter and can't see much because it is so dark. Annie likes to leave her tent flaps closed. She is making her famous black bottom pie. What exactly is black bottom pie? It looks like she might be using mud. Her home is bare except for some pie tins and stinky clothing strewn about.

special_tiles.title: Johnny's Tent
special_tiles.description: Pegleg Johnny opens the tent flap as though he was expecting you. He greets you with an "Ahoy, Matey" and invites you in. It's cozy in here for being a tent. He has a few extra wooden legs propped up against the wall. And lying on the table is the biggest pot of jewels you have ever seen. He catches you eyeing his booty. "Don't even think about breathing a word of this to the others."

special_tiles.title: Willie's Tent
special_tiles.description: Some bones hang from the doorway. Willie's tent is well lit with several lanterns. He has many swords and is sharpening one right now.

special_tiles.title: Sid's Tent
special_tiles.description: The mood in here is dismal. You can see how Sid got his name. He's not a very friendly chap and he is of course scowlin' at you. You feel like leaving. He keeps muttering Arrrgh...his tent is bare. This pirate needs a friend.

special_tiles.title: Wilma's Tent
special_tiles.description:
The tent is empty. There is a note on the table which reads:
Ahoy!
Meet me at Cannonball Cate's for good times and bring your friends.

special_tiles.title: Cate's Tent
special_tiles.description: Sounds like a party in there. You open the tent and see that Cate and Wilma are having a good time. Doing a pirate jig, and playing games with the various cannonballs in the tent. It smells wonderful in here. Must be molasses cookies.

special_tiles.title: Toby's Tent
special_tiles.description: Oh my feathers! This pirate must have plucked a lot of birds to get all these feathers. Toby is lounging in a chair while his toes are being tickled with a feather. His hearty laugh draws you in.

special_tiles.title: Maddog Robert's Tent
special_tiles.description: Peaking inside the tent flap, all you really see is a mattress for sleeping, a few articles of clothing bunched in the corner and a small lantern hanging from a hook in the center.

special_tiles.title: McGee's Tent
special_tiles.description: The tent flaps are closed. You walk in and you immediately start coughing. Now you understand why they are always shut. The tent's location by the fire is not ideal. McGee greets you and shakes your hand. Trying not to make a disgusted face you slyly wipe your hand on your pants. His tent is nice if you can get over the smoke problem. A few works of art featuring ships hang on the walls, the table has a large bowl of fruit on it. He offers you some tea but when he grabs the cup it slips out of his hand and breaks, same thing with the next one and the one after that until he has no cups left. You are thinking that a pair of gloves might come in handy for him.

special_tiles.title: Horse Anatomy
special_tiles.description: ^T5Find the correct part of the horse.^BMhorseanatomy^R1^T4View the top scores for this game^BSHHorse Anatomy^R1^X^Z

special_tiles.title: Southern View Hammock
special_tiles.description: An extremely peaceful and serene area.  You decide to relax and bask in the warm sun.^X^Z

special_tiles.title: Fourfinger Frank's Shack
special_tiles.description: Franks shack here is simple and neat.  You can tell that Frank spends a lot of his time reading.

special_tiles.title: Shimerin Shimm's Shack
special_tiles.description: Shimm apparently deals with a lot of paperwork.  There are stacks and stacks of papers around the small shack here.  From quick glances it appears that she translates coded Pirate messages.

special_tiles.title: Captain Solomon's Hut
special_tiles.description: There are piles of old papers, scrolls and maps everywhere.  Most of the piles seem to be on a rough old desk.  A parrot is sitting in the corner chatting away.

special_tiles.title: Silver Mary's Hut
special_tiles.description: This hut has a fresh, clean air to it.  Everything appears to be in its correct place with pieces of silver hanging from the walls.  Silver Mary obviously takes pride in her hut.

special_tiles.title: Silvertooth Sam's Cabin
special_tiles.description: Everywhere are anchors shining and silver coins laid strewn about on the ground.  Maps are hung all over.   Many have X's on them.  A chest is by his bed, but don't touch it.  He didn't get the name SilverTooth for nothing.

special_tiles.title: Bart's Hut
special_tiles.description: There are old ship parts piled everywhere in the cabin.  There are some interesting anchors decoratively placed around the room and sea maps spread out on the table in the middle.

special_tiles.title: Squalid Nathaniel's Hut
special_tiles.description: Peeking in the door, the hut is incredibly clean.  There is also a sweet smell in the air.  Sort of like flowers even though you haven't actually seen any yet.

special_tiles.title: Pirate Ship
special_tiles.description: This large ship has crossbone emblems painted everywhere.  You notice the ship's captain staring at you impatiently.

special_tiles.description: There is sand and rocks spread all over throughout the cabin.  Not surprising being the surroundings of the cabin.  It would be amazing if he could keep this stuff from getting in.

special_tiles.title: Lighthouse

special_tiles.description: Ahead of you stands a nasty looking pirate guarding the bridge.  There is also a hole in the bridge which you hope you'll be able to cross sometime soon.

Went exploring around Ice Isle. I'm either still gone or over at Mikko's.
-Matti

special_tiles.description: This area is where the art competitions take place.  Be sure to participate even if you don't feel like you can draw well.  Often creativity is the most important factor to help you win!!

special_tiles.title: Fish Calling Point
special_tiles.description: Here is a large yellow stone with a pictograph of an ear chiseled into it.  If you know the name of the fish who lives here, you can call him from this location.  If you don't know the correct name, you can get away by digging near the center of the isle.

special_tiles.title: Dusty's Shack
special_tiles.description: Dusty's shack is.. well... dusty.  You see someone wrote their name in the dust on the table next to the door.  You see a short gray haired man on the other side of the shack looking through a dusty book.

special_tiles.title: Sea Horse Weeds

special_tiles.title: Atreyu's Cabin
special_tiles.description: Atreyu's cabin is full of strange and wonderful things.  There are paintings of giant snails and rock creatures are on the wall.

special_tiles.title: Elizabeth's Lodge
special_tiles.description: Elizabeth's lodge is spacious with oversized, beautiful furnishings.  It strikes you as odd that it's decorated nicely but it's a mess!  There are piles of pinecones everywhere...

special_tiles.title: Sara's Island Retreat
special_tiles.description: This is a quaint little vacation home.  The kitchen cabinets are painted a jade color and white cotton curtains embroidered with strawberries and small green vines flutter in the open kitchen windows.  The china displayed in the nearby hutch is decorated with a delicate strawberry pattern.

special_tiles.title: The Skulls!
special_tiles.description: This flag smashed into the sand makes it very obvious whose territory you are entering.  Better hope you're friends with someone in there.

special_tiles.title: Wington Horse Haven
special_tiles.description: As you enter the barn you see the owner bent over what appears to be an old metal work table in the tack room. She is busily doing something to a pile of wire and gems in front of her. As you look around you realize how beautiful the barn is with wonderful lines of flashing lights illuminating everything.

special_tiles.title: Draft Arena
special_tiles.description:
Choose a strong horse for this competition.
Be careful when viewing other things before your competition begins.  It may cause your race to not start up.  ^T4View the best times for this arena^BSTDraft Arena^R1

special_tiles.title: Coconut Bounce
special_tiles.description: Help the monkey collect giant coconuts!^T5Coconut Bounce^BMcoconutbounce^R1^T4View the top scores for this game^BSHCoconut Bounce^R1^X^Z

special_tiles.title: AmeriBrit
special_tiles.description: Try to guess which is the British word/spelling and which is the American version.^T5AmeriBrit^BMameribrit^R1^T4View the top scores for this game^BSHAmeriBrit^R1^X^Z

special_tiles.title: Oak Tree
special_tiles.description: Somehow, inside this Oak Tree you are in a tiny room with a little chair and table and small shelves with books and decorations on them.  There is a small pile in the corner of acorns and a hole in the wall just large enough for shells to be thrown out.

special_tiles.title: Synonymousness
special_tiles.description: Pick the correct word out of the short list that has the same meaning as the one shown.^T5Synonymousness^BMsynonyms^R1^T4View the top scores for this game^BSHSynonymousness^R1^X^Z

special_tiles.title: Tail End Bank
special_tiles.description:
Though it looks large outside, upon entering you realize this bank is quite small. It appears to have been hurriedly built in order to serve the needs of the ranch owners of Tail Isle.
Note: A max of $9,999,999,999 is allowed to be held in the bank and a max of $2,147,483,647 on hand.

special_tiles.title: Greig's Cabin
special_tiles.description: There are notes posted all over the walls in this small, rustic cabin.  Apparently Grieg is a very forgetful feller.  At least he remembers to remind himself!   Although you see some notes have fallen to the floor.

special_tiles.title: Santon's Special Gear
special_tiles.description: Glancing around, the store is filled with odd shaped tack.  Most doesn't look like it would even fit a horse and most of it is bright, beautiful colors.

special_tiles.title: Jungle Temple #1
special_tiles.description: Here lies ancient symbols.  Maybe you should try to assemble them. ^T6Jungle Temple^BMjungletemple.swf?BOARD=1&QUEST=777&j=^R1^X^Z

special_tiles.title: Jungle Temple #2
special_tiles.description: Here lies ancient symbols.  Maybe you should try to assemble them. ^T6Jungle Temple^BMjungletemple.swf?BOARD=2&QUEST=778&j=^R1^X^Z

special_tiles.title: Kiah's Hut
special_tiles.description: The strong smell of herbs rushes at you as you approach the hut. Upon entering, you see herbs hanging all around the small hut. Kiah is standing over a table grinding some down with a mortar and pestle.

special_tiles.title: Halian's Hut
special_tiles.description: Entering the hut you see Halian studying what appears to be a very engrossing rock game. There are several books laying around and beautiful pieces of artwork scattered over the walls.

special_tiles.title: Ilom's Hut
special_tiles.description:
This hut looks small from the outside, but is actually quite spacious once inside. There is a neatly written note sitting on a table just inside the doorway.
Welcome to my home. I am currently taking my daily stroll around the meadow. Feel free to search for me if you like.
-Ilom

special_tiles.title: Nomasonto's Hut
special_tiles.description: The small hut is well furnished with a table and other furniture made from the local trees.  Beautiful dishes are perfectly arranged on a counter along the wall.

special_tiles.title: Manco's Hut
special_tiles.description: Manco's hut is very clean considering the large number of sacks piled neatly against the back wall of his hut.  On the walls are detailed maps of the surrounding islands with all the best walnut groves circled in red.

special_tiles.title: Jungle Temple #3
special_tiles.description: Here lies ancient symbols.  Maybe you should try to assemble them. ^T6Jungle Temple^BMjungletemple.swf?BOARD=3&QUEST=779&j=^R1^X^Z

special_tiles.description: Here lies ancient symbols.  Maybe you should try to assemble them. ^T6Jungle Temple^BMjungletemple.swf?BOARD=4&QUEST=780&j=^R1^X^Z

special_tiles.description: Here lies ancient symbols.  Maybe you should try to assemble them. ^T6Jungle Temple^BMjungletemple.swf?BOARD=5&QUEST=781&j=^R1^X^Z

special_tiles.title: Inigo Webster's Metalworks Shop
special_tiles.description: Walking into the cabin you see a huge fantastically colored copper weaving. It looks like a virtual waterfall  all shimmering bronze and copper.   Up against the opposite wall there is a piece of framed art unlike anything you have ever seen. It is a Matisse done on embossed copper and mounted in a frame of brushed aluminum.  You can hear a loud pounding sound from the back room and there is a sharp smell in the air.

special_tiles.title: Jungle Temple #6
special_tiles.description: Here lies ancient symbols.  Maybe you should try to assemble them. ^T6Jungle Temple^BMjungletemple.swf?BOARD=6&QUEST=782&j=^R1  ^X^Z

special_tiles.title: Cookie's Treehouse
special_tiles.description: As you step into the house, the most wonderful aroma greets you - a delicious blend of fruits and pastry. A recipe book is open on the table and recipe cards are scattered all around the room. A young woman with a chef's hat perched on her dark brown curls is tying an apron around her waist.

special_tiles.title: Jungle Temple #7
special_tiles.description: Here lies ancient symbols.  Maybe you should try to assemble them. ^T6Jungle Temple^BMjungletemple.swf?BOARD=7&QUEST=783&j=^R1^X^Z
