special_tiles.title: The Brick Home of the Third Little Pig
special_tiles.description: A sturdily built brick residence, capable of withstanding all weathers.

special_tiles.title: The Wooden Home of the Second Little Pig
special_tiles.description: A well-built residence made of logs and planks; sturdy, but possibly not the best choice in severe conditions.

special_tiles.title: The Lair of the Big, Bad Wolf
special_tiles.description: Under a pile of leaves (or something) is a ramshakle lean-to, stuffed with old blankets, old clothes, and loose fur.

special_tiles.title: The Straw Home of the First Little Pig
special_tiles.description: A small, hastily and inexpensively built residence that barely keeps out the rain.
Lying under the tree, his head propped against an old saddle, is a sun-tanned, work-hardened cowboy.

special_tiles.title: Mod Isle
special_tiles.description: A place to get away from the constant stalking and buddy adding that is the life of a mod.
special_tiles.autoplay_swf: cloudsign.swf?TEXT=Welcome to Mod Isle.  Sit and relax.&junk=

special_tiles.title: Mod Relaxation Cabin
special_tiles.description: Come in and put your feet up! This is a private place to relax and get away. There is a friendly woman in the kitchen ready to serve you if you need any refreshments.

special_tiles.title: Aislin's Home
special_tiles.description: This cozy little home belongs to Aislin, a young woman who obviously loves her horse. There are photos hung all over the walls and models strewn across shelves and tables, all depicting the same, sweet faced grey mare you see standing just outside the window.

special_tiles.title: Unicorn Uniter
special_tiles.description: The Unicorn Uniter's hair is pure white, but it's impossible to tell whether he's old or young.  His features speak of much patient study, and his voice is quiet and calm.

special_tiles.title: Pegasus Uniter
special_tiles.description: The Pegasus Uniter is either a very old cowboy or a very young elf; it's hard to say.  Around him is a paddock full of restful shade, in which flying horses nuzzle and nosh.

special_tiles.title: Horse Leaser
special_tiles.description: This large ranch offers fully tacked horses for daily rent for use as transportation.

special_tiles.title: The Home of the Cat Family
special_tiles.description: A loud mewling comes from this house--along with a harried mother's voice.

special_tiles.title: Sandcastle Moat #20
special_tiles.description: ^T6Straighten out the Moat^BMsandcastlemoat.swf?BOARD=20&QUEST=2991&j=^R1^X^Z

special_tiles.title: The Phoenix's Nest
special_tiles.description: Under these trees, you find a very curious nest--the sides are a mixture of some kind of sparkling dust and ... ashes?

special_tiles.title: Aladdin's Castle
special_tiles.description: Here sits a small castle, European in style, but, when you look more closely, with a hint of Oriental splendor.

special_tiles.title: Jungle Observation Deck Access
special_tiles.description: Against the trees here are heavily braced ramps and platforms leading up into the jungle canopy.

special_tiles.title: Welcome Sign
special_tiles.description: Very small print under the main title on the sign reads, "Handsome Princes Always Welcome" and under that, "No Solicitors."
special_tiles.autoplay_swf: cloudsign.swf?TEXT=Welcome to the Castle of Princess Lilianna&junk=

special_tiles.title: The Castle of Princess Lilianna
special_tiles.description: This grand castle is sumptuous to the core; silk and velvet flags and curtains flap easily in the breeze, and gold and silver ornaments glitter everywhere.

special_tiles.title: Welcome Sign
special_tiles.description: In small print, the sign reads, "Guests Always Welcome For Dinner."
special_tiles.autoplay_swf: cloudsign.swf?TEXT=Welcome to the Home of the Big Bad Wolf&junk=

special_tiles.title: Sam McGee's Cabin
special_tiles.description: You walk into a very sparsly decorated cabin, which has obviously never known a feminine touch. There are model boats of all shapes and sizes littering the various surfaces. The cabin belongs to Sam McGee, and he shares it with his grandson Davy, who cares for him.

special_tiles.title: Marisole's Home
special_tiles.description: Marisole's home is very spacious and elegant. There is an air of richness eminating from every corner. Grand decorations hang on the walls, including a large, beautifully woven tapestry that looks like it outlines a lengthy family tree.

special_tiles.title: Forest Cottage
special_tiles.description: With its thatched roof and ivy covered stone walls, this little cottage seems right out of a fairytale. The view from every window is lovely, looking out over a serene forest pool and nestled among the pine trees.

special_tiles.title: Grandmother's House
special_tiles.description: This charming little house is the home of Grandmother Riding Hood.  The smell of apple pie and cinnamon buns overwhelms you as you pass!

special_tiles.title: The Hoods' Home
special_tiles.description: This small house is the home of the Red Riding Hood Family.
You see a lonely looking Joshua Tree.

special_tiles.title: Welcome Sign
special_tiles.description: Appended to the sign is a notice saying, "Genies Wanted. Apply Within."
special_tiles.autoplay_swf: cloudsign.swf?TEXT=Welcome to the Castle of Aladdin&junk=

special_tiles.title: Pecos Bill's Home
special_tiles.description: This rough little cowboy house is completely out of place here amongst the clouds.

special_tiles.title: Rapunzel's Tower
special_tiles.description: In front of you is a tall tower with a small window all the way at the top.  Looking around the base there doesn't appear to be a door anywhere.

special_tiles.title: The Home of Peter Pumpkin Eater
Winchell's Hut
special_tiles.description:
Right away you notice something odd about this place. The outside is draped with ropes and strips of fabric. Parts of large baskets are strewn all around.
As you peer in, you see a hut decorated with star charts, weather maps and large pictures of the occupant, standing on what looks like a lot of cotton candy.

special_tiles.title: Welcome Sign
special_tiles.description: All over are sights never before seen.  Purple, sparkling trees, cotton candy trees and odd houses all set on soft, squishy clouds.

special_tiles.title: Candy House
special_tiles.description: As you open the gingerbread door to the candy house, you see that the inside is just as elaborately decorated with candy as the outside.  You are tempted to begin eating the gingerbread and icing walls, but realize that might not be a good idea.  You hear a ruckus coming from the kitchen.  Something is on the kitchen counter and you have to look ever so closely to see whats going on...

special_tiles.title: Exit to Tropicton
special_tiles.description: The teleport in front of you will drop you in Tropicton.  Be sure that is where you want to go before stepping in!

special_tiles.title: Exit to Earton
special_tiles.description: The teleport in front of you will drop you in Earton.  Be sure that is where you want to go before stepping in!

special_tiles.title: Exit to Hotton
special_tiles.description: The teleport in front of you will drop you in Hotton.  Be sure that is where you want to go before stepping in!

special_tiles.title: Pumpkin Patch
special_tiles.description: The most perfect pumpkins you have ever seen.  Your horse is looking for something to nibble on, but a large raven in the dead tree nearby scares you off!

special_tiles.title: The Dumpty Residence
special_tiles.description: This quaint cottage is made of finely mortered river stones with arched windows and front door. You wonder how the stone house doesn't fall through the clouds. The Cloud Isles are obviously magical!

special_tiles.title: A Small Cottage
special_tiles.description: This quaint cottage has a thatched roof the color of a ripe tomato and a charming front door that is the bright green of spring leaves. Such an interesting little home!

special_tiles.title: Simple Jumping Arena
special_tiles.description:
Compete against others in this competition that is based less on your horse's stats. Only 6 horses can compete at one time.  Be aware.  Horse stats and special tack play very little to no part in the scoring of this arena.
Be careful when viewing other things before your competition begins.  It may cause it to not start up.^T4View the top scores for this arena^BSHSimple Jumping Arena^R1

All around this tiny island are bits of metal which you can only assume are parts of something.  Although some of them are broken, and many are beyond repair, everything is laid out in an orderly fashion, with lines and arrows drawn in the sand, connecting one to the other in complicated ways.  You walk very carefully so as to disturb nothing.

special_tiles.title: Horse Isle Foal Adoption Center
special_tiles.description: The Horse Isle Foal Adoption Center is a great way for you to introduce a weanling foal to the wider world!  Not only will these foals make excellent companions for your horses, but your care will help them learn and grow strong, smart and confident.

special_tiles.title: Pirate Cave #2
special_tiles.description: This cave looks too difficult for a single person to explore,  best to bring a friend with!

special_tiles.title: Direction Sign
special_tiles.description:
This sign looks brand new, but is quite off the beaten path. The directions don't seem overly helpful either. North: Tropicton
South: The Horse Whisperer

special_tiles.title: The Jungle Horse Whisperer
special_tiles.description: Welcome to the Horse Whisperer. For $50,000 he can try to locate a wild horse of a particular breed and point it out on the map to you. If there probably isn't a wild horse of that breed right now, he will tell you that also for a lesser fee of $10,000. Be aware. Any other traveler could pay to see the same breed and might beat you to the horse you chose to find. First to catch a wild horse gets to keep it. There is no guarantee that you can reach the horse even if it is found. It will still cost you the full amount!

special_tiles.title: The Saddle Horse Whisperer
special_tiles.description: Welcome to the Horse Whisperer. For $50,000 he can try to locate a wild horse of a particular breed and point it out on the map to you. If there probably isn't a wild horse of that breed right now, he will tell you that also for a lesser fee of $10,000. Be aware. Any other traveler could pay to see the same breed and might beat you to the horse you chose to find. First to catch a wild horse gets to keep it. There is no guarantee that you can reach the horse even if it is found. It will still cost you the full amount!

special_tiles.title: Pirate Cave #1
special_tiles.description: This cave looks too difficult for a single person to explore,  best to bring a friend with!

special_tiles.title: Pirate Cave #3
special_tiles.description: This cave looks too difficult for a single person to explore,  best to bring a friend with!

special_tiles.title: Pirate Cave #4
special_tiles.description: This cave looks too difficult for a single person to explore,  best to bring a friend with!

special_tiles.title: Type in the correct answer in the box below:
special_tiles.description: I may play on any server, however if I make more than one account (meaning different usernames), there is a good chance all of my accounts will be _____.

special_tiles.title: Type the correct answer into the box below:
special_tiles.description: The chat filter flags some words and changes others.  If I try to avoid, or cheat, the filter to use colorful language, the mods will ____ me.

special_tiles.title: Type the correct answer in the box below:
special_tiles.description: When I agree to trade another player for a horse or object, I must complete my half of the trade.  If I don't, my account will be ____.

special_tiles.title: Type the correct answer into the box below:
special_tiles.description: I am ____ for anything that happens on my own account, even if someone else gets on when I get up for a minute.

special_tiles.title: Pirate Cave #5
special_tiles.description: This cave looks too difficult for a single person to explore,  best to bring a friend with!

special_tiles.title: The Office of Sergeant Major Percy Stickler, Ret.
special_tiles.description: Welcome to the Brig.  Everything here is austere and grey, but the walls are lined with portraits; Patton, Napoleon, several Caesars, Sun Tsu, Atilla and Montgomery figure prominently among them.  A bronze statue of Alexander riding Bucephalos sits on his desk--upon which you notice a newly-arrived dispatch with your own name on it!

special_tiles.title: Horse Isle Retailer
special_tiles.description:
The Horse Isle Retailer could really use some help with their money.
^T5Give correct change^BMretailer.swf^R1^X^Z

special_tiles.title: Emma's Cabin
special_tiles.description: On a table in this house is a sketch of the island, with drawings showing the positions of proposed buildings.  Perhaps the owner is walking around the island taking further measurements?

special_tiles.title: Mino's and Lelu's home
special_tiles.description: This is a very modest home, almost Zen-like in its simplicity. There is a general feeling that is a true refuge and sanctuary.  Lelu is a beautiful woman who greets you at the door with a calm demeanor.

special_tiles.title: Hide and Seek
special_tiles.description: Multiplayer minigame of hide and seek

special_tiles.title: The Spice Shoppe
special_tiles.description: As you walk into the shop you are overwhelmed by the aroma from all the different spices. There are several large and small containers with all the different spices throughout the store. You see the owner busily working in the back and as she notices you she comes to the counter.

special_tiles.title: Cave of the Blue Dragon
special_tiles.description: The entrance to this cavern is of lapis lazuli and sodalite, with kyanite and sapphire glistening from cracks in the rock.  The area is warm, and the dragon who lives here must be powerful indeed!

special_tiles.title: The Cave of the Red Dragon
special_tiles.description: The large cavern entrance here is marbled with veins of carnelian, cinnabar and copper.  Billows of steam and smoke issue forth from it, as if some great steam engine lie inside, softly breathing as if asleep.  You approach with the utmost caution.

special_tiles.title: The Cave of the Purple Dragon
special_tiles.description: The cave here is smaller than the others, but no less beautiful.  Crystals of amethyst and tanzanite glitter from the bluestone walls of the cave.

special_tiles.title: The Cavern of the Green Dragon
special_tiles.description: Before you is an enormous cave of olivine and jade.  Veins of beryl, tourmaline and emerald glitter in the rock, and a steady stream of smoke alerts you to the fact that a dragon--a very large dragon--is in residence.

special_tiles.title: The Cavern of the Cyan Dragon
special_tiles.description: Here is a magnificent cavern of aquamarine and amazonite, and some of the palest blue jade.  You can't tell from outside whether there is a dragon here right now or not, but there has certainly been one here very recently--and it might soon return.

special_tiles.title: Broken Sign
special_tiles.description:
There is a very old broken message here which you believe reads:
After days of trial and error, I discovered a simple pattern to getting through the Fire Flower patch! All you have to do is notice that there are two different flower types, and then just avoid the ...
It is broken off at that point!

special_tiles.title: The Cavern of the Yellow Dragon
special_tiles.description: This lovely cavern is made of onyx and ochre; topazes and sulphur crystals grow all over it.  Steam and smoke announce that a dragon is here now.

special_tiles.title: The Cavern of the Magenta Dragon
special_tiles.description: The cavern here is low and wide; it must accomodate wings of a gigantic size.  Rhodochrosite and lepidolite make up this cavern, and rubies and rhodonite streak its surface.  A single spiral of smoke and steam issues from one corner; but it is so slight that perhaps it does not mean the dragon is actually at home.

special_tiles.title: The Palace of Princess Pookie
special_tiles.description:
You walk (with some trepidation) into a throne room full of pink and yellow and green.... and teddy bears and .... shoes... and more shoes... and even more shoes....
In the midst of it all sits a girl of about 11, but trying very hard (and failing miserably) to look and act like a Cool Teenager. She slouches on her throne, peers at you imperiously, and snaps gum. She doesn't speak to you: she texts you by scribbling on a chalkboard.

special_tiles.title: Old Sign
special_tiles.description:
There is an old wooden sign here, barely legible:
The mud holes! They interconnect the many rooms in this area... I was lost in here for days, be careful, going back in a mud hole will not always bring you back to where you were!

special_tiles.title: The House of Amariel
special_tiles.description: The only word you can think of to describe this house is "subtle."  There is nothing striking in the house, but the whole atmosphere itself is curiously elegant.    On one side near a window sits a woman.  Her hair is green, but you could swear it is not dyed that color.  She is old, and she sits in a wheelchair with a meticlously embroidered blanket over her legs.  She has an almost startling way of looking at you through piercing grey eyes, as if she sees you, but only as a detail in a much larger picture.

special_tiles.title: Xiang's Home
special_tiles.description: Xiang's home is a maze of boxes, shelves and tables, all piled high with small and curious objects collected from near and far.

special_tiles.title: Pella's Cave
special_tiles.description:
This "cave" is nothing more than a roof to keep rainwater out of a hole leading deep into the ground. There is a dated note on the wall which reads:

Hello, I've gone out for a snack. If this note is still hanging here by the above date, I am probably lost. Send help!

The date is almost four days ago!

special_tiles.title: Kirby's Hut
special_tiles.description: When you walk inside Kirby's hut, you are greeted by the cacophony of insects crunching, crawling, fluttering, clicking, rasping and slithering about. Kirby obviously believes in studying them up close and face to face. Thankfully, the bugs are safely inside screened enclosures.

special_tiles.title: Bruce and Colina's Home
special_tiles.description: Outside, this home looks like all the others on this street, but come inside and you are in a different world.  Pictures of the Highlands adorn the wall, and the Johnston clan tartan can be seen everywhere.
Somewhere in the far distance, you can hear the skirling of bagpipes.
The music of the bagpipes wafts over you from somewhere near.

special_tiles.title: Guardians
special_tiles.description: You are between the Crystal Labyrinth Guardians, which is the entrance to the massive 7 crystal labyrinth.

special_tiles.title: Guardian
special_tiles.description: To the north stands a giant labyrinth guardian.  In its burning mouth are Magenta crystals.

special_tiles.title: Guardian
special_tiles.description: To the north stands a giant labyrinth guardian.  In its burning mouth are Yellow crystals.

special_tiles.title: Guardian
special_tiles.description: To the north stands a giant labyrinth guardian.  In its burning mouth are Cyan crystals.

special_tiles.title: Guardian
special_tiles.description: To the north stands a giant labyrinth guardian.  In its burning mouth are Green crystals.

special_tiles.title: Guardian
special_tiles.description: To the north stands a giant labyrinth guardian.  In its burning mouth are Purple crystals.

special_tiles.title: Guardian
special_tiles.description: To the north stands a giant labyrinth guardian.  In its burning mouth are Blue crystals.

special_tiles.title: Guardian
special_tiles.description: To the north stands a giant labyrinth guardian.  In its burning mouth are Red crystals.

special_tiles.title: Martine's Hut
special_tiles.description: Martine's hut is full of books on the history of Horse Isle, many of which, it seems, she's written herself.

special_tiles.title: Selena's Hut
special_tiles.description: Inside this rather small hut hang stars, planets, and galaxies... unfortunately you find you don't recognize a single one!  Selena, dressed in ... a gown made out of camouflage material? ... and many glittery scarves, rushes toward you as if she couldn't be happier you are here!

special_tiles.title: The Cabin of Sir Sleepwell
special_tiles.description: This house by the sea is decorated with old broadswords, shields with coats of arms, lances and announcements of tournaments.

special_tiles.title: Direction Sign
special_tiles.description:
NORTH:Earton
EAST:Horse Isle Equestrian Park
SOUTH:Appleton

special_tiles.title: Welcome to the Horse Isle Equestrian Park
special_tiles.description: The brand-new sign reads: "Welcome to the Horse Isle Equestrian Park.  Our deluxe facilities showcase the finest Racers, Hunter/Jumpers, Dressage Horses and Drafters.  All the competitions involve more advanced riders allowing for higher winnings.  Enjoy your stay!"

special_tiles.title: Odette Pond
special_tiles.description: Beautiful swans glide by on the glistening pond.  On the shore, a green frog winks at you!  You look again and you see a small splash as he dives under a nearby lilypad.

special_tiles.title: Odette Pond
special_tiles.description: Beautiful swans glide by on the glistening pond.  On the shore, a green frog winks at you!  You look again and you see a small splash as he dives under a nearby lilypad.

special_tiles.title: Pro Draft Arena
special_tiles.description:
Choose a strong horse for this competition.
The entry fee is $10,000, making the winnings much more valuable.
Be careful when viewing other things before your competition begins.  It may cause your race to not start up.  ^T4View the best times for this arena^BSTDraft Arena^R1

special_tiles.title: Pro Dressage Arena
special_tiles.description:
Compete against others in this competition  that is mainly based off your horse's conformation and groom.  Only 5 horses can compete at one time.
The entry fee is $10,000, making the winnings much more valuable.
Be careful when viewing other things before your competition begins.  It may cause it to not start up.
^T4View the top scores for this arena^BSHDressage Arena^R1

special_tiles.title: Pro Racing Arena
special_tiles.description:
Compete against others in this competition  that is mainly based off your horse's Speed and Endurance.  Only 6 horses can compete at one time.
The entry fee is $10,000, making the winnings much more valuable.
Be careful when viewing other things before your competition begins.  It may cause your race to not start up.
^T4View the top scores for this Event^BSHRacing Arena^R1

special_tiles.title: Pro Jumping Arena
special_tiles.description:
Compete against others in this competition  that is mainly based off your horse's Strength and Speed.  Only 6 horses can compete at one time.
The entry fee is $10,000, making the winnings much more valuable.
Be careful when viewing other things before your competition begins.  It may cause it to not start up.
^T4View the top scores for this arena^BSHJumping Arena^R1

special_tiles.title: Penfold's Hut
special_tiles.description: Penfold is an avid fan of guinea pigs; his guinea pigs live in elaborate habitats, and several ribbons and prizes line the walls.

special_tiles.title: Vesuvia's Hut
special_tiles.description:
A beautiful poster of an erupting volcano on the wall just inside the door reads: "Volcanology is the study of volcanoes, lava, magma, and related geological phenomena. The term volcanology is derived from the Latin word Vulcan, the Roman god of fire." There are other charts and maps covering the walls.
A woman sitting at a desk in the corner hunched over something looks up suddenly and welcomes you with a smile.

special_tiles.title: Patrick's General Supplies
special_tiles.description: The shelves are stuffed full with most anything you would need for both you or your horse.

special_tiles.title: Lenny's Home and Workshop
special_tiles.description: Spread out over every inch of every surface indoors and out here are stones in all shapes and sizes, stone chips and most especially, stone dust. There are also tools; chissels, mallets, hammers, pins, awls and many others besides.

special_tiles.title: Equestrian Park Wagon Station
special_tiles.description: Stepping off the wagon here is like stepping into a different world.  The Horse Isle Equestrian Park is a place of pomp, and all around you are Horse Isle's most splendid equine athletes.

special_tiles.title: Equestrian Park Stables
special_tiles.description: All around are magnificent, athletic horses.  This stable is obviously for the best and the price appears to reflect that.

special_tiles.title: Hoof Isle Gazebo
special_tiles.description: This lovely little structure is somehow cool, breezy and inviting; the perfect place to meet friends and enjoy a lemonade on a beautiful summer's day.

special_tiles.title: Sunshine Meadows Gazebo
special_tiles.description: The breeze over the forest brings the scent of pines and oaks to this beautiful meeting place.  So relaxing and refreshing, a fabulous place to listen to birdsong.

special_tiles.title: Hoof Isle Playground
special_tiles.description: This cool, shaded playground is full of delights for kids young and old.  The equipment here has seen many years of happy use and has been lovingly cared for.

special_tiles.title: Lornbacoll's Lair
special_tiles.description: Something about this lair speaks of mystery, intrigue and suspense.  It's hard to say exactly what it is, but something about the place exudes mystery and an unmistakeable elegance.

special_tiles.title: Desert Foal Adoption Center
special_tiles.description: Cool breezes from the ocean make this an idyllic place; the pastures here have horse foals, and zebra foals, llama crias and camel calves as well, all gambolling together playfully.

special_tiles.title: Cupid's Abode
special_tiles.description: An odd looking Tree house covered in red hearts on a light pink background.  Upon walking inside you see heart shaped furniture and valentines pasted all over the walls.

special_tiles.title: Home of Venus
special_tiles.description: Upon entering this pink colored treehouse you find a young woman sitting amongst a bunch of heart shaped bottles and concentrating on some sort of concoction.

special_tiles.title: Home of Eros
special_tiles.description: As you enter this red house you see a lot of pictures placed about on the walls.  After studying them, you realize they are pictures of Eros and his wife.

special_tiles.title: Cupid's Work
special_tiles.description: Try to catch two hearts together to help Cupid with his work! ^T6Cupid's Work^BMcupid^R1^T4View the top scores for this game^BSHCupids Work^R1^X^Z

special_tiles.title: Rashida's Hut
special_tiles.description:
All around you are board games.  Some are stacked up against the walls, others are hanging on the wall as a sort of decoration.  Rashida, sitting at a table in the center of the hut, seems deep in thought while staring at a checkerboard.
^T6Help Rashida arrange the checkers.^BMcheckerslide.swf?QUEST=1852&j=^R1

special_tiles.title: Koko's Residence
special_tiles.description: It is barely possible to walk inside this large cabin.  There are papers, clothes and other miscellaneous things strewn everywhere.  Koko seems not quite in her right mind as she is jumping and dancing around in the middle of the whole mess.

special_tiles.title: Dewy Glade
special_tiles.description: You see tiny cloven hoof prints in the dew.

special_tiles.title: Mystical Creature Adoption Center
special_tiles.description: A baby dragon is a rare and wonderful thing!  Their affinity for horses is curious and unexpected--but incredibly strong!  The same can be said about the mystical phoenix and young Gryphon.  They all require a special home though, with someone who is willing to work for them; so they are very expensive!

special_tiles.title: Iambe's Favorite Clearing
special_tiles.description: The trees and plants in this tiny clearing seem to have grown into a natural bower.

special_tiles.title: Capri's Preferred Clearing
special_tiles.description: A sense of peace imbues this lovely place.  Tall, flowering plants around the edge of the clearing have formed themselves into a decorative latticework.

special_tiles.title: Fauna's Chosen Spot
special_tiles.description: Although it seemed small on the map, somehow this clearing widened and brightened the moment you stepped in.  You're dazzled by the quality of the sunlight streaming through the branches.

special_tiles.title: Nerina's Hut
special_tiles.description: Inside you see posters of whales and other sea creatures covering the walls.  The outside of this hut is covered in many shells and interesting rocks.

special_tiles.title: Flicka's hut.
special_tiles.description: Walking in through the netted door you're surprised by what you see.  All around, beetles of every color and shape line the walls.  A few scurry on the floor and you look down, making sure you don't step on any while making your way over to a clear patch.  There stands a young woman.  In her hand she holds a giant...bug?

special_tiles.title: Omand's Deck #5
special_tiles.description: There are ramps here leading south, down to the jungle floor.

special_tiles.title: Jungle Observation Deck Access
special_tiles.description: Against the trees here are heavily braced ramps and platforms leading up into the jungle canopy.

special_tiles.title: Jungle Observation Deck Access
special_tiles.description: Against the trees here are heavily braced ramps and platforms leading up into the jungle canopy.

special_tiles.title: Omand's Deck #6
special_tiles.description: There are ramps here leading north, down to the jungle floor.

special_tiles.title: Jungle Observation Deck Access
special_tiles.description: Against the trees here are heavily braced ramps and platforms leading up into the jungle canopy.

special_tiles.title: Omand's Deck #14
special_tiles.description: There are ramps leading south and down to the jungle floor here, there are also platforms leading off to the west.

special_tiles.title: Omand's Deck #17
special_tiles.description: There are ramps leading south and down to the jungle floor here.

special_tiles.title: Jungle Observation Deck Access
special_tiles.description: Against the trees here are heavily braced ramps and platforms leading up into the jungle canopy.

special_tiles.title: Jungle Observation Deck Access
special_tiles.description: Against the trees here are heavily braced ramps and platforms leading up into the jungle canopy.

special_tiles.title: Omand's Deck #18
special_tiles.description: There are ramps leading north and down to the jungle floor here.

special_tiles.title: Large Comfortable Hut
special_tiles.description: Conveniently located near the oasis, this hut has a rather low roof, but it is large, bright and cheery, and features a wide doorway.

special_tiles.title: Western Tack Shop
special_tiles.description: Once you enter you are overwhelmed with the smell of leather.  There are leather pieces, cloth pieces and cotton all over.  Vats in the corner are filled with the different colored dyes and all sorts of tools are piled on tables and in cabinets.

special_tiles.title: Island View Hammock
special_tiles.description: An extremely peaceful and serene area.  You decide to relax and bask in the warm sun.^X^Z

special_tiles.title: Island View Hammock
special_tiles.description: An extremely peaceful and serene area.  You decide to relax and bask in the warm sun.^X^Z

special_tiles.title: Tranquility Pond
special_tiles.description: A peaceful and beautiful scene, this pond is not only a place to fish and relax, but a great thirst quencher for any horses.

special_tiles.title: Serene Art Room
special_tiles.description: In this cabin there is a giant easel with lots of pens. Everyone who enters is encouraged to go ahead and doodle alone or together.

special_tiles.title: Tranquil Art Room
special_tiles.description: In this cabin there is a giant easel with lots of pens. Everyone who enters is encouraged to go ahead and doodle alone or together.

special_tiles.title: Tranquil Wishing Well
special_tiles.description: It's peaceful here. Take a break and wish for some good fortune.

special_tiles.title: The Serenity Shop
special_tiles.description: It's hard at first to realize that this place is a store.  It's first and foremost a home, and mainly a huge kitchen, with all the frills and other homey touches you'd expect to see at your own grandmother's house.  Everything seems warm and hearty and so very welcoming that you relax immediately upon entering. The "store" has a little of this and a little of that, but you very quickly realize that the one thing it has infinite supplies of is....gossip!

special_tiles.title: Drill Conformation Trainer
special_tiles.description: The finest groomers, massage therapists and fitness experts all work here to make your horses show to their maximum potential.

special_tiles.title: Drill Endurance Trainer
special_tiles.description: This complex course of low hills and long straightaways is perfect for conditioning the endurance horse.

special_tiles.title: Drill Speed Trainer
special_tiles.description: This beautifully maintained course of wide curves and long straightaways is perfect for conditioning the racing horse.

special_tiles.title: Drill Strength Trainer
special_tiles.description: This carefully groomed, sandy arena features high and wide jumps and a special harness area and is perfect for conditioning the jumping or pulling horse.

special_tiles.title: Drill Agility Trainer
special_tiles.description: This complex course of switchbacks, and arena full of cavaletti, is perfect for conditioning the agility horse.

special_tiles.title: Drill Isle Docks
special_tiles.description: Of all the docks you've been to on these isles, this is certainly the classiest.  Everything is "ship shape" here, neatly stowed and sparkling clean.  Photographs of famous horses who've come through here line the walls.

special_tiles.title: Welcome to Drill Isle!
special_tiles.description: The sign reads, "Featuring the Finest Trainers in All Disciplines, Ready to Serve the Discriminating Customer."

special_tiles.title: Serenity Docks
special_tiles.description: This dock is overrun with photographs, of famous horses and horse-trainers, and also of great adventurers who have landed on these isles.  Some of the photographs are very old indeed, but all are carefully preserved.  There is also a very obvious "seahorse" theme about the place.  Models and paintings of seahorses are everywhere, and a tank of live ones decorates a table to one side.

special_tiles.title: Welcome to Starfish Isle!
special_tiles.description: An isle where the sand is warm, the breezes are cool and the people are friendly!

special_tiles.title: Mortimer's Cabin
special_tiles.description: This is the home of Mortimer, the groundskeeper of Starfish Isle.  Against the fence and walls are all kinds of rakes, clippers, bags of mulch, compost piles and potted plants.

special_tiles.title: Starfish Isle Docks
special_tiles.description: Nobody's dusted this harbor structure in ages.  Nor swabbed its decks, nor given it a new coat of paint.  It doesn't look bad.... it just looks like it hasn't changed in many, many a year!

special_tiles.title: Small Pond
special_tiles.description: A small, beautiful pond.  A perfect place to fish or let your horse get a quick drink.

special_tiles.title: A Sunbleached Skull
special_tiles.description: The skull is draped in sparkling strands of spider silk. Looking through the empty eye sockets, you can see the interior of the skull is filled with chaotic webbing that seems to have no rhyme or reason. An obsidian-black spider hangs upside down in the middle of the web. The bright red hourglass on her abdomen is clearly meant as a warning.

special_tiles.title: A Sunbleached Skull
special_tiles.description: Looks like another victim of the scorching desert heat.

special_tiles.title: A Sunbleached Skull
special_tiles.description: Looks like another victim of the scorching desert heat.

special_tiles.title: A Sunbleached Skull
special_tiles.description: Looks like another victim of the scorching desert heat.

special_tiles.title: A Sunbleached Skull
special_tiles.description: This skull is filled with spider webbing.

special_tiles.title: A Sunbleached Skull
special_tiles.description: This is all that is left of some poor animal. It appears a huge tarantula is living here.

special_tiles.title: Cozy Igloo
special_tiles.description: Inside it looks cold but quite comfortable at the same time.  It is sparsely decorated, but there is a fish shape carved into the wall for apparent decoration.

special_tiles.title: Lighthouse
special_tiles.description: This lighthouse sits high above the seawall and is well-protected from the pounding waves. A brilliant beam of light sweeps a welcoming beacon over the sea.

special_tiles.title: Iris Pettel's Flower Garden
special_tiles.description: This small garden is in full bloom with many different kinds of beautiful flowers.  This must be where Iris gets her flowers for her shop.

special_tiles.title: Fritz's Cabin
special_tiles.description: The cabin is small, but obviously well lived in.  There are some truffles on the table top along with assorted other forest goodies.  Fritz continually pokes his head out the window to look out at his pig in the garden next to the house.

special_tiles.title: Fritz's Garden
special_tiles.description: This is a pleasant and comfortable home, alongside of which is a remarkably neat garden--considering it's home to a pig!  Around the garden posts are several holes where the pig seems to have been searching for something.

special_tiles.title: Sani & Yepa's Home
special_tiles.description: Sani and and his wife Yepa are the revered elders of the Desert Isles.  They live quietly still practicing the ancient traditions.  Yepa is a basket weaver and Sani is a shaman and sand artist.  They welcome all who come in peace.

special_tiles.title: Wu Kung's Treehouse
special_tiles.description: You look up to see an ancient monkey in his tree.  Could he really be practicing martial arts katas at his age?

special_tiles.title: Master Lau's Lair
special_tiles.description: That's odd, here is this large aging tiger stretched out under his tree practicing, always practicing his katas.

special_tiles.title: Master Hoa's Tree
special_tiles.description: You look up in the tree and, believe it or not, there's an old white crane gracefully doing katas.

special_tiles.title: Master Shua's Den
special_tiles.description: There's a large blue snake slithering in the sand.  Wait a minute, he seems to be slithering in distinctive patterns.  Wow, he's doing katas too!

special_tiles.title: Master Tang's Flower Patch
special_tiles.description: You almost can't see anyone, Master Tang blends into the greenery so well, but wait, over there, the leaves are rustling.  You find Master Tang practicing his katas.

special_tiles.title: Hyrokkin's Home
special_tiles.description: You enter this house and realize that everything inside and outside are just a bit larger than normal.  The house sits on the shore facing the sea as if waiting for something.  The decor is best described as retro Viking/Norse, fitting for this resident.

special_tiles.title: The Home of the Three Bears
special_tiles.description: What should be a small, quaint, cozy home is flooded with light.  You see film canisters, cameramen, and various assistants running around excitedly!

special_tiles.title: Tuque's Workshop
special_tiles.description: This tiny workshop is filled with sawdust, curls of shaven wood, and half finished projects.  Blueprints of boats adorn the walls, as if they were only for decoration.

special_tiles.title: Bowen and Peru's house
special_tiles.description: A very large, yet simple, two room house. The clean white walls in the main room boast a few lovely wooden masks, and a heavy oak table takes pride of place.

special_tiles.title: Lava Isle Gristmill
special_tiles.description: A pair of huge burr millstones overwhelm this building.

special_tiles.title: Simple Gifts Farm
special_tiles.description: Simplicity at its finest in this house!  You see a large brick fireplace where cooking is done, a spinning wheel, and an old-fashioned butter churn.  Wait... who lives like this?

special_tiles.title: Simple Gifts Potager
special_tiles.description: A sign reads "Private Garden - Please Do Not Trample!"

special_tiles.title: The Awlaboard Cabin
special_tiles.description: Delectable herb plants grow beneath the windows. Wonderful smells emanate from the kitchen of this cozy cabin, causing your stomach to rumble loudly. There is a delightful doll collection sitting on a small bed.

special_tiles.title: The Good Egg
special_tiles.description: The Good Egg is the storefront for a small egg and butter outfit.  A chalkboard placard you see when you walk in lists market prices.  At the bottom of the placard, in very bold writing, you read: "We do not sell milk or cream!"

special_tiles.title: The Good Egg, U-Pick-It Garden
special_tiles.description: A sign reads "Pick your own veggies!  Prices per pound listed in store."  You don't see any veggies here at first glance.

special_tiles.title: Dr. Fernlove's Laboratory
special_tiles.description: A man of science is fast at work among pallets of seedlings.  Dr. Fernlove's specialty is selective plant breeding to increase crop yields.  His hobby though, through some secret method, is producing near-mythic fruits and vegetables to surprise and delight.  His magnum opus is a cranberry the size of an apple and tasting of... pear...?

special_tiles.title: Mandy's Pasture
special_tiles.description: This small, well kept pasture goes right up to the house, so that the pasture residents can stick their heads inside for a visit.

special_tiles.title: Jungle Foal Adoption Center
special_tiles.description: Here in this remarkably cool jungle clearing sits a comfortable stable for young foals, happy and bright and waiting for a new home with you.

special_tiles.title: Carly Cobbler's House
special_tiles.description: The house seems a little larger than most homes here, and you notice moving boxes strewn all around.  Behind Carly there is mayhem with children and toys all over the place!  Just how many children does this woman have?

special_tiles.title: Fish Calling Point
special_tiles.description: Here is a large green stone with a pictograph of an ear chiseled into it.  If you know the name of the fish who lives here, you can call him from this location.  If you don't know the correct name, you can get away by digging near the center of the isle.

special_tiles.title: Fish Calling Point
special_tiles.description: Here is a large purple stone with a pictograph of an ear chiseled into it.  If you know the name of the fish who lives here, you can call him from this location.  If you don't know the correct name, you can get away by digging near the center of the isle.
There is a shovel mark in the grass here, but it's not very deep.
There is a shovel mark in the grass here, but it's not very deep.
There is a shovel mark in the grass here, but it's not very deep.

special_tiles.title: Fish Calling Point
special_tiles.description: Here is a large blue stone with a pictograph of an ear chiseled into it.  If you know the name of the fish who lives here, you can call him from this location.  If you don't know the correct name, you can get away by digging near the center of the isle.
There is a shovel mark in the grass here, but it's not very deep.

special_tiles.title: Pony Express Headquarters
special_tiles.description: Twine and paper are arranged in an orderly fashion against one wall and you see large plastic tubes spitting out and organizing some of the mail into giant bins.  A nice gentlemanly fellow quickly checks his list and stamps each box as they flow smoothly over the counter.

special_tiles.title: Witherton Jumping Arena
special_tiles.description:
Compete against others in this competition  that is based less on your horse's stats. Only 6 horses can compete at one time.  Be aware.  Horse stats and special tack play very little to no part in the scoring of this arena.
Be careful when viewing other things before your competition begins.  It may cause it to not start up.^T4View the top scores for this arena^BSHSimple Jumping Arena^R1

special_tiles.title: Witherton Farrier
special_tiles.description: This is a new building, but the farrier himself has been at his job for a very long time.

special_tiles.title: Witherton Livery
special_tiles.description: This bright, airy, fresh-smelling stable is the perfect place to board your tired horses.
The south wall of the maze here has a mark on it.
You almost trip into a little hole filled with small twigs, grasses, and soft fur.

special_tiles.title: Mother Goose's Home
special_tiles.description: Her home is fairly simple, and very neat. She has a few bookcases crammed with various bedtime stories, fairy tales, and classic children's stories. Not too surprisingly, she keeps a couple of geese as pets. You hope they don't bite.

special_tiles.title: Gingerbread Bakery
special_tiles.description: Welcome to Hansel and Gretel's brand new bakery! The aroma permiating the surrounding area is drawing you into the shop.  Everything looks so good, and of course, Gingerbread is their specialty!

special_tiles.title: Sun-bleached Skeleton
special_tiles.description: Another pirate skeleton. Bet this one was part of the skeleton crew!

special_tiles.title: Sun-bleached Skeleton
special_tiles.description: No bones about it, with the skull seeming to smile up at you, this skeleton gives you the jitters.

special_tiles.title: Newly Built Cabin
special_tiles.description: You are standing in a pleasant cabin filled with books and blueprints on a variety of roofing styles and methods.  There is an assortment of roofing supplies neatly stacked in one corner.

special_tiles.title: Construction Site
special_tiles.description: The construction site is a buzz with activity!  There's a hole about ten foot deep with dirt tossed about on all sides.  Cats with hardhats are moving dirt with heavy machinery, sawing boards, nailing nails, and all while the Foreman shouts instructions over the noise.

special_tiles.title: Katinka's Cottage
special_tiles.description: The cabin is warm and welcoming, with neat stacks of hand knit goods all around.

special_tiles.title: Leasa's Garden
special_tiles.description: Here is a beautiful rock garden full of perennials and a colorful annual or two.  The smell from the mock orange tree is delicious.

special_tiles.title: Leasa's Cottage
special_tiles.description: This cottage is warm and cozy with a quilt or two decorating the wall and over the back of the sofa.   Pictures of children and grandchildren are hanging on the walls and sitting on small endtables.  The smell of a delicious pie baking wafts from the kitchen.

special_tiles.title: Torrid Isle Docks
special_tiles.description: A small boat is tied to the side of the dock ready to take passengers.   The dock is cluttered with crates and nets though, making a bit difficult to get to board the boat.  Should you be low on money, it would be best to speak with the owner.

special_tiles.title: Oasis
special_tiles.description: A cooling breeze wafts over this large oasis.  Your horse is enjoying a nice roll in the shade of one of the palm trees.

special_tiles.title: Oasis
special_tiles.description: A cooling breeze wafts over this large oasis.  Your horse is enjoying a nice roll in the shade of one of the palm trees.

special_tiles.title: Bee's Nest
special_tiles.description: There are lots of bees here! If you want though, you could try to take their honeycomb...^T4Steal Honeycomb from Bees^BMbees.swf?m=^R1

special_tiles.title: Pyramid #10
special_tiles.description: If you wish,  you could explore the Labyrinth within this pyramid!!!^T6Explore Pyramid^BMpyramidmaze.swf?MAZE=10&QUEST=2977&j=^R1^X^Z

special_tiles.title: Laurence's Hut
special_tiles.description: The walls of this bright, airy hut have been swathed in fabric, in simulation of a sumptuous desert tent.  Rattan furniture and gold plated decor are polished to gleaming, and the floor of a lustrous orange wood was recently waxed and shined with care.

special_tiles.title: Vivian's House
special_tiles.description: Here lives a true horsewoman.  You see books on horses, pictures of horses, statues of horses, horse tack and equipment, riding apparel... but no sign of an actual horse anywhere.

special_tiles.title: Maude's Hut
special_tiles.description: This hut is a disaster.  Papers, toys, craft supplies, dishes, books, yarn, string, swatches of fabric, bits of cotton (and much more) are stacked in huge piles over every horizontal surface, including the floor.  Perhaps the occupants have just moved in.

special_tiles.title: Vine Isle Docks
special_tiles.description: This small dock looks like it is barely used.  There are vines covering the dock and the small building.

special_tiles.title: Viney Rocks
special_tiles.description: This rock shop is tiny but has every possible spot filled with different gems, stones and jewelry.  The small storekeeper appears engrossed in whatever stone he is currently looking at.

special_tiles.title: Warm and Cozy Treehouse
special_tiles.description: You enter a treehouse in the jungle and get the immediate smells of dried florals and art supplies.^T6Paint Esther's Picture^BMpainting.swf?PAINTING=15&QUEST=3443&j=^R1

special_tiles.title: The Hot Spring of Frigid Meadows
special_tiles.description: A mist slowly rises from this warm spring.  You can feel heat coming from it, and there is a smell of minerals in the mist.

special_tiles.title: Clarissa's Cabin
special_tiles.description: This is a remarkably comfortable cabin for one so far to the north.

special_tiles.title: Nedrick's House
special_tiles.description: The walls of this house are completely full of mounted insects in frames.

special_tiles.title: Polar Isle Docks
special_tiles.description: This is a pleasant enough dock; there is very little breeze here.  But it would be much nicer were it a little warmer.

special_tiles.title: Jada's Cottage
special_tiles.description: This cozy cottage offers a warm fireplace to sit beside.^T6Paint Jada's Picture^BMpainting.swf?PAINTING=13&QUEST=3444&j=^R1

special_tiles.title: A well built snowman.
special_tiles.description: The air crackles and smells like magic in this particular spot.

special_tiles.title: Ted's House
special_tiles.description: This small home seems rather poorly insulated for being on such a cold isle.  There is dust all over and it appears to be very drafty, making it quite chilly in places despite the fire in the fireplace.

special_tiles.title: Sandcastle Moat #21
special_tiles.description: ^T6Straighten out the Moat^BMsandcastlemoat.swf?BOARD=21&QUEST=3049&j=^R1^X^Z

special_tiles.title: Olivia's Cabin
special_tiles.description: The cabin is small, cozy and warm.  In the kitchen you can smell a pie in the oven and there are cookies sitting out on the counter.

special_tiles.title: Alexi's Cabin
special_tiles.description: Alexi is crouched over a table peering at the paper that is scattered all around her.  She seems quite glad to see you.

special_tiles.title: Tree House
special_tiles.description: A relatively empty, but spacious set of rooms high up off the ground.

special_tiles.title: A Small, Cozy Cabin
special_tiles.description: A well-made and sturdy home. There are sea maps on the walls and a telescope pointing out the window.

special_tiles.title: North Shore View Hammock
special_tiles.description: An extremely peaceful and serene area.  You decide to relax and bask in the warm sun.^X^Z

special_tiles.title: North Shore View Hammock
special_tiles.description: An extremely peaceful and serene area.  You decide to relax and bask in the warm sun.^X^Z

special_tiles.title: Hat Isle Specific Store
special_tiles.description: The Hat Isle Specific Store sells this one might not expect of pirates--and the wares are of exceptional quality.

special_tiles.title: Hat Isle Rowboat
special_tiles.description: One look is enough to tell you that the owner of this rowboat would rather be anywhere apart from here.  He's so eager to get back that the trip back to Skullton is free.

special_tiles.title: DO NOT ENTER Sign
special_tiles.description: The sign here makes it abundantly clear that company is not wanted.  Could they be referring to you though? ^X^Z

special_tiles.title: DO NOT ENTER Sign
special_tiles.description: The sign here makes it abundantly clear that company is not wanted.  Could they be referring to you though? ^X^Z

special_tiles.title: DO NOT ENTER Sign
special_tiles.description: The sign here makes it abundantly clear that company is not wanted.  Could they be referring to you though? ^X^Z

special_tiles.title: Beebonnet Buck's Hut
special_tiles.description: The interior of the hut is bestrewn with scraps of yarn. There is a cat in the corner batting at the pieces.

special_tiles.title: No-Navel Nancy's Hut
special_tiles.description: As you walk in the hut, you notice a peculiar milky smell. You look up to see that the interior of the ceiling is studded with coconut shells! No-Navel Nancy catches you looking up and gives you a glare, as if to say, "What you lookin' at?"

special_tiles.title: Foolin' Fred's Hut
special_tiles.description: You're assaulted by color the moment you walk in the door- Foolin' Fred has painted the interior walls in great swirls of yellows, reds, greens, and blues.

special_tiles.title: Mums-The-Word Maria's Tent
special_tiles.description: The tent is jam-packed with books and papers. It looks as though the tent is the seat of pirate academia- if pirates indeed value academics. Mums-The-Word Maria sits in the middle of it all in an armchair, chewing a candy pipe, facing a most incongruously placed empty couch.

special_tiles.title: Boxy Bernie's Tent
special_tiles.description: Boxy Bernie clearly loves rats. It looks like they are swarming the inside of his tent! But as you look closer, you realize there's some sort of method to this madness. The rats seem to have specific runs where they're contained in one area of the tent, and some of them are swimming around a small pool. As you watch, one leaps up onto a platform in the middle of the pool and starts grooming his whiskers. Boxy Bernie checks his pocket watch and notes down the time.

special_tiles.title: Whorl Isle Dock
special_tiles.description: This dock has an amazing view of the snow isles off in the distance. The breeze is always a bit nippy here and the water a bit choppy. That doesn't stop the locals from sailing around the bend though. The dockhouse has plenty of seating if you'd like to watch the boats go in and out- if you count vast piles of mail-stuffed sacks "seating"- and an enormous picture of a stern-looking woman in a military uniform hanging on the wall.

special_tiles.title: Whorl Isle Observatory
special_tiles.description: A small, private observatory with a rather front-heavy refracting telescope.

special_tiles.title: Gytha's House
special_tiles.description: The house is completely spotless- floors polished, tablecloth without a single crumb, china ornaments on the mantel glistening. Gytha reigns in the middle of it all, sprawled in an overstuffed floral armchair, her feet up on an ottoman.

special_tiles.title: Esmerelda's Home
special_tiles.description: As you enter the house, it seems deserted. The oil lamp isn't lit and the silence is almost eerie. As you look around, you have the prickling sensation that you're being watched- and suddenly you see Esmerelda over in the corner, looking straight at you.

special_tiles.title: Ismond's Cabin
special_tiles.description: The shutters are locked up tight and the door is locked, bolted, and chained shut.
The shoreline on this side of the isle seems hard, as though it's been regularly trampled by someone pacing.
The shoreline on this side of the isle seems hard, as though it's been regularly trampled by someone pacing.
The shoreline on this side of the isle seems hard, as though it's been regularly trampled by someone pacing.
The shoreline on this side of the isle seems hard, as though it's been regularly trampled by someone pacing.

special_tiles.title: Ring Pond
special_tiles.description: This small pond is shaped almost exactly like the isle itself.  It's almost like someone shaped it themselves instead of nature doing the work.

special_tiles.title: Ring Isle Observatory
special_tiles.description: The Ring Isle Observatory is a public observatory, which can be used by anyone lucky enough to be able to get time on the telescope's schedule.  A large bulletin board and calendar on the wall shows that telescope time is booked many months in advance.

special_tiles.title: Web Isle Docks
special_tiles.description: The Web Isle Docks appear to be very old, but have been carefully maintained.

special_tiles.title: Ring Isle Dock House
special_tiles.description: The Ring Isle Dockhouse is practically empty, as if nobody's been here for a long time.  You can make out a trail of footprints in the dust though, from the front door to the desk and back.

special_tiles.title: Jane and Gillian's House
special_tiles.description: The aroma of fresh-cut wood pervades the small house- almost stronger than the smell of wet dog.

special_tiles.title: Andrea's Home
special_tiles.description: Andrea's house has a small lean-to attached to the back, from which you can hear cheeps and caws. You peer around the corner and see the whole shed is full of birds!

special_tiles.title: Mythic Shoppe
special_tiles.description: The Mythic Shoppe is very clean, and seems to sell only two things: golden pellets and cyan pellets.

special_tiles.title: Kelda's Home
special_tiles.description: The house is filled with brightly painted nesting dolls and Dala horses. Over in the corner, you see a workbench with additional dolls and horses in various degrees of completion, along with paint, brushes, sandpaper and wood carving tools.

special_tiles.title: Lilibeth's Hut
special_tiles.description: You are amazed at all of the dried flowers in Lilibeth's home.  There are flowers and wreaths hanging everywhere!

special_tiles.title: Woody's Hut
special_tiles.description: Woody's hut is filled with animals of all descriptions as well as dolls and native figurines, all carved by Woody.  In the corner you see an ample supply of wood waiting for Woody's skillful touch.

special_tiles.title: Chanda's Hut
special_tiles.description: You find Chanda dipping a candle in a series of pots of colorful wax.  Her hut is filled with more candles than you have ever seen.^T6Paint Chanda's Picture^BMpainting.swf?PAINTING=14&QUEST=3441&j=^R1

special_tiles.title: Alton's Hut
special_tiles.description: Alton is sitting at a counter carefully cutting pieces of fruit.   The entire hut is filled with flower arangements that look good enough to eat....wait a minute that daisy is made from a melon!  They really are good enough to eat!!!

special_tiles.title: Shoneah's Hut
special_tiles.description: You find Shoneah hunched over a work table too busy to notice you. He has examples of his fine jewelry designs displayed around his hut.

special_tiles.title: Web Isle Wishing Well
special_tiles.description: Though it appears relatively dilapidated, this wishing well still appears to work.

special_tiles.title: Balloon Game
special_tiles.description:
Collect the blue bubbles and avoid the red ones! ^T6Hot Air Balloon^BMhotairballoon^R1
^T4View the top scores for this game^BSHHot Air Balloon^R1
^X^Z

special_tiles.title: A Gryphon's Lair
special_tiles.description: As you carefully peer into this cave you can see two Gryphons hard at work building a nest.

special_tiles.title: Apollo's Hut
special_tiles.description: As you enter, you notice a golden charriot parked next to the hut.  Once inside, it's as bright as can be!  You almost need sunglasses to counter the glare.  Even Apollo, himself, is glowing!

special_tiles.title: Scoria Rowboat
special_tiles.description: Well, it's not the most seaworthy-looking vessel- covered in seaweed and smelling strongly of salt and jellyfish- but you suppose it will get you from point A to point B. You hope, anyway.

special_tiles.title: Basalt Isle Rowboat
special_tiles.description: This decidedly seaweed-covered vessel looks like it could hardly cross a creek, let alone an ocean, but it did after all get you here...

special_tiles.title: A Gryphon's Lair
special_tiles.description: As you carefully peer into this cave, you see two Gryphons. One is sitting on the nest and the other is standing guard. Looks like the one just laid an egg!

special_tiles.title: Turquoise Jewelry Workshop
special_tiles.description: Inside the workshop there's a desk where Lapis works on all the jewelry that comes into her workshop.  There are bins of tools as well as metal and leather remnants on the desk and floor.

special_tiles.title: Basalt Isle Boardwalk
special_tiles.description: Water dragons lounge across the weathered boards of the dock, flicking their long tails into the sea as they soak up the sun.

special_tiles.title: Hanska's and Christel's Home
special_tiles.description: The little house is scrupulously neat, but entire walls are filled with shelves of toymaking supplies.
It looks like someone was fishing here.

special_tiles.title: Shilling Cottage
special_tiles.description: The name of this house is a bit of a non-sequitur, but don't ask Mal or Polly about it. They'll just look at each other, then at the portrait of a woman hanging on the wall. Then one of them will say "On the bottom!" and they'll both double over in laughter. It's not worth the explanation.

special_tiles.title: Martina's Cabin
special_tiles.description: Her walls are covered with lists and swatches and pictures. Everything a premier wedding planner could need.

special_tiles.title: Fluff's Cave
special_tiles.description: The few steps between the glittery stone walls of the cave represent a mere fraction of an acre... and independence.

special_tiles.title: Astrid's Home
special_tiles.description: The few timbers of wall not taken up by windows are covered by hand-painted star charts.

special_tiles.title: Horn Isle Docks
special_tiles.description: Welcome to Horn Isle Docks.  Be aware of clouds and high winds from all sides of the isle.

special_tiles.title: Yellow Brick Isle Dock
special_tiles.description: A small, rickety looking dock house with a couple sail boats tied to a sun warn dock.

special_tiles.title: A Curious Upright Boulder
special_tiles.description: There are odd petroglyphs carved on the surface.
On this side of the rock, strange symbols are carved along one edge.

special_tiles.title: Treasure Isle Pirate Resort Office
special_tiles.description: This looks like a hotel lobby complete with a front desk. Theres a handsome woman behind the desk smiling at you. Behind the desk is a chalk board with space to enter the names of guests after each tent number.  Doesn't look like there are any keys. Makes sense. After all, you can't lock a tent!

special_tiles.title: DO NOT ENTER Sign
special_tiles.description: The sign here makes it abundantly clear that company is not wanted.  Could they be referring to you though? ^X^Z

special_tiles.title: Western Hammock
special_tiles.description: An extremely peaceful and serene area.  You decide to relax and bask in the warm sun.^X^Z

special_tiles.title: Eastern Hammock
special_tiles.description: An extremely peaceful and serene area.  You decide to relax and bask in the warm sun.^X^Z

special_tiles.title: Treasure Isle Resort Souvenir and Gift Shop
Pirate's Pool
special_tiles.description: Where you can swim with the fishes and still make it back for lunch!

special_tiles.title: Pirate's Pool
special_tiles.description: Where you can swim with the fishes and still make it back for lunch!

special_tiles.title: Mapmaker Mike's Tent
special_tiles.description: You find a drafting table in the back of the tent with a basket full of parchments and vellums next to it.  There are several pots of ink near the table and maps and pen and ink sketches hung all over the walls of the tent.

special_tiles.title: Ye Olde Grog Shack on the Beach
special_tiles.description: There is a banner stretched across the shack which reads; "Coming Soon"

special_tiles.title: Archy and Mehitabel's Cabin
special_tiles.description: Mehitabel is seated at a desk by the window. There is a bulletin board above it with various bills and lists tacked to it.  She looks up when she hears you enter.

special_tiles.title: Treasure Isle Resort Souvenir and Gift Shop
Rowboat
special_tiles.description: A small, but sturdy, rowboat ready to head off the isle at a moment's notice.

special_tiles.title: Beach Equipment
special_tiles.description: Everything you could need to enjoy the beach and surf. Game equipment, surf boards and snorkeling equipment available for the guests.

special_tiles.title: Illiana's Hut
special_tiles.description: A small hut, partially shaded under some palm trees, with neatly manicured surroundings.

special_tiles.title: Upada's Home
special_tiles.description: A small space filled with stacks of paper making the room seem even smaller.

special_tiles.title: Gem Slider
special_tiles.description:

special_tiles.title: Nikara's Fish and Rocks
special_tiles.description: A small shop filled to the brim with anything to do with fishing along with a counter of assorted gems and beach findings.

special_tiles.title: A Sunbleached Skull
special_tiles.description: You see a weathered skull. Looking closely, you see webbing around one of the eye sockets. You've spied a spider's den!

special_tiles.description: Seaweed is tangled up with bits of driftwood and seashells.

special_tiles.title: Sun-bleached Skeleton
special_tiles.description: Yikes! This poor fellow looks like he took a nap in the hammock and never woke up! Someone must have rolled him out onto the sand and just left him here.

special_tiles.title: Flotsam
special_tiles.description: Seaweed is tangled up with bits of driftwood and seashells.

special_tiles.title: Dead Gnarled Tree
special_tiles.description: The dead tree isn't a palm tree. You wonder what other kind of tree would grow in a place like this.

special_tiles.title: Sun-bleached Skeleton
special_tiles.description: Yikes! You can see through the rib cage right to the backbone of this poor soul. A shiver just ran up your spine! You can almost hear the tune to Dem Bones, Dem Bones, Dem....Dry Bones!

special_tiles.title: The cozy home of Indigo and Bettina
special_tiles.description: The workbench has assorted carving tools, and small ebony carved figurines on it. There is a beautifully carved kitchen table with two carved chairs.

special_tiles.title: Cordovan & Cecilia's House
special_tiles.description: The home is filled with interesting aromas. There are different herbs and flowers hanging from the rafters that look like they are in various stages of drying. A rack with skiens of wool sits next to a spinning wheel.

special_tiles.title: Howling Moon Boutique & Sweets
special_tiles.description: The charming store has assorted handcrafted island goods including alpaca hair throws, ebony carved figurines, beautifully crafted guitars and coconut body products. A large sign at the counter says "Sweets for the Sweet!"  A glass display case holds an assortment of berry pies. Looks like there is a special on freshly churned vanilla ice cream today.

special_tiles.title: Home of Twyla and Victor
special_tiles.description: The house is filled with the scrumptious smell of coconut. A series of shelves are lined with stacks of homemade soaps and jars of lotion.

special_tiles.title: Isaac's House
special_tiles.description: Isaac's home has at least a dozen guitars standing up against the walls. They are all made of the same dark wood, but have different designs inlaid in different colors.

special_tiles.title: Dog Isle Community Center
special_tiles.description: Well this is a change. Unlike the past times you have stopped by, there are no signs of any kind of crazy celebration having taken place recently. The Community Center is spotless. The shoe and hat that was under one of the tables and moved to the fireplace mantle are still there. A sign in the shape of a tulip says CLOSED - remember to mark your calendar for the upcoming Spring Extravaganza!^X^Z

special_tiles.title: Oringo's Tree House
special_tiles.description: Through the slightly cracked door, you can't see much.

special_tiles.title: Dog Isle Rowboat
special_tiles.description: A tiny rowboat is tied to a rock that is tossed up on the beach to keep the boat from floating away.  The tattered, small boat barely looks seaworthy.

special_tiles.title: Vine Isle Rowboat
special_tiles.description: A small, tattered boat is sitting on shore, waiting to cross the water.  It barely looks seaworthy.

special_tiles.title: Vladyk and Svetlana's Cabin
special_tiles.description: This cabin is delightfully cozy. There are beautiful embroidered curtains on the windows, wooden carved pictures of elk and deer on the walls and a crackling fireplace that gives off plenty of heat.

special_tiles.title: Ruslan and Olena's Cabin
special_tiles.description: This is an older but well kept cabin that is on the larger side. There are traditional Ukrainian embroidered linens on the table, and decorative pillows on the sofa. The entire place looks welcoming and colorful.

special_tiles.title: Vasyl and Lesia's Cabin
special_tiles.description: This cabin is warm and cozy. There is a display case filled with beautifully decorated eggs in the traditional Ukrainian style called pysanky. A small work bench next to the case has assorted tools and eggs in different stages of completion. Looks like the artist lives here!
Looks like a pair of Joshua Trees.
Looks like a Joshua Tree.

special_tiles.title: Cabin Isle Dock
special_tiles.description: Looking out from the dock, you see the green of many small islands in the distance. Suddenly, a humpback whale breaches the surf just off to your left, arcs up, up, up and then falls back into the water with a mighty splash. Whew! That was exciting.

special_tiles.title: The Whoa and Go General Store
special_tiles.description: Cabin Isle's general store is quaint but cozy. Looks like it caters to the local residence.

special_tiles.title: Anathema's Cabin
special_tiles.description: The windows and door to the cabin are flung wide open, as if the person who lived here didn't have a care in the world. The lacey curtains are made from pixie dust stitched delicately together with the thread of silver linings. Who could have made such an amazing thing? There are spools and spools of silver lining stacked against the wall.

special_tiles.title: Frannie Oakley's Log Cabin
special_tiles.description: This cabin is very well cared for. Everything is clean and spotless.

special_tiles.title: Glacier Docks
special_tiles.description: A wicked wind blows snow flurries around and you can see slivers of ice nestled in the cracks of the dock boards. Inside the small cabin, there's a fire burning in a corner fireplace that warms the place up enough to make it cozy, despite how chilly it is outside.
The ripples in the sand look like golden waves.

special_tiles.title: A Roaring Bonfire
special_tiles.description: Wow. This bonfire puts off some nice heat. It would be great for toasting marshmallows! Or frying up some tasty cinnemon churros.

special_tiles.title: A Small Thatched House
special_tiles.description: Sand has blown in through the open windows and now covers the floorboards in a series of ripples. You wonder if the house has been abandoned.

special_tiles.title: A Snowman!
special_tiles.description: With as cold as it is here, you doubt the snowman will be melting anytime soon.
A perfect little pond for ice skating!

special_tiles.title: A Frozen Pond
special_tiles.description: You can see where chunks have been carved from the ice. Looks like those areas are filling in and freezing over already!

special_tiles.title: A Water Barrel
special_tiles.description: This water barrel has been knocked over and the water has spilled out.

special_tiles.title: Jocosa's Beach Shack
special_tiles.description: The home is elevated high above the beach, giving you a great view of ocean waves. There are assorted sea shell arrangements hanging about the room. Obviously, Jocosa is into sea shells. She's probably out on the beach collecting shells right now.

special_tiles.title: Home of Horacio & Vega
special_tiles.description: This rambling home is filled with the laughter of a large and happy family. Vega has several different chile riestras hanging in her kitchen. You suspect that she probably does a lot of cooking with all those different varieties.There is something baking in the oven right now that smells delicious!

special_tiles.title: Home of Ociel & Bonita
special_tiles.description: Ociel and Bonita have a lovely and cozy little abode. Oribella, their infant daughter, is sleeping in a baby hammock. How sweet is that?

special_tiles.title: Witherton Library
special_tiles.description: A small, stuffy room filled with books on every surface.  This includes stacks upon stacks sitting on the floor.

special_tiles.title: A Strange And Stilted Hut
special_tiles.description: The stilts that hold up the hut look like.... could it be? yes! Chicken legs! Huge chicken legs are holding up the place! There are two small windows that look like eyes and a door that looks like an open chicken's beak. This is a very strange hut!

special_tiles.title: A Gryphon's Lair
special_tiles.description: As you carefully peer into this cave you can see a Gryphon sitting upon a nest of two eggs.

special_tiles.title: A Gryphon's Lair
special_tiles.description: As you look into this cave, you can see a nest filled wtth the pieces of shattered shells. Looks like these gryphons have hatched and left their nest already.

special_tiles.description: Oh look! Sandy shed shells of crab are caught in the ocean debris here.

special_tiles.description: Look at those waves pounding the shoreline!

special_tiles.title: A Disturbance In The Sand!
special_tiles.description: Wow. Lots of little holes line the shoreline here. Ah ha! You saw a crab peek out of a hole. Cute little critter!

special_tiles.title: Ocean Turbulence
special_tiles.description: This part of the island sure takes a beating from the ocean waves.

special_tiles.title: Belwyn's Cave
special_tiles.description: Built entirely out of obsidian chunks, the cave blends into the island soil so well you can barely see it. There are plenty of notions and potions shelved along the left side of the cave. A comfy looking cot is along the right side. Other than those things, the cave is pretty barren.
